1734
1735void CodeGenModule::getDefaultFunctionAttributes(StringRef Name,
1736 bool HasOptnone,
1737 bool AttrOnCallSite,
1738 llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs) {
1739 // OptimizeNoneAttr takes precedence over -Os or -Oz. No warning needed.
1740 if (!HasOptnone) {
1741 if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize)
1742 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
1743 if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize == 2)
1744 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
1745 }
1746
1747 if (CodeGenOpts.DisableRedZone)
1748 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoRedZone);
1749 if (CodeGenOpts.IndirectTlsSegRefs)
1750 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("indirect-tls-seg-refs");
1751 if (CodeGenOpts.NoImplicitFloat)
1752 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoImplicitFloat);
1753
1754 if (AttrOnCallSite) {
1755 // Attributes that should go on the call site only.
1756 if (!CodeGenOpts.SimplifyLibCalls ||
1757 CodeGenOpts.isNoBuiltinFunc(Name.data()))
1758 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
1759 if (!CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName.empty())
1760 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("trap-func-name", CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName);
1761 } else {
1762 StringRef FpKind;
1763 switch (CodeGenOpts.getFramePointer()) {
1764 case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::None:
1765 FpKind = "none";
1766 break;
1767 case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf:
1768 FpKind = "non-leaf";
1769 break;
1770 case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::All:
1771 FpKind = "all";
1772 break;
1773 }
1774 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("frame-pointer", FpKind);
1775
1776 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("less-precise-fpmad",
1777 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.LessPreciseFPMAD));
1778
1779 if (CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
1780 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NullPointerIsValid);
1781
1782 if (CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode != llvm::DenormalMode::getIEEE())
1783 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("denormal-fp-math",
1784 CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode.str());
1785 if (CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode != CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode) {
1786 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(
1787 "denormal-fp-math-f32",
1788 CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode.str());
1789 }
1790
1791 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-trapping-math",
1792 llvm::toStringRef(LangOpts.getFPExceptionMode() ==
1793 LangOptions::FPE_Ignore));
1794
1795 // Strict (compliant) code is the default, so only add this attribute to
1796 // indicate that we are trying to workaround a problem case.
1797 if (!CodeGenOpts.StrictFloatCastOverflow)
1798 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("strict-float-cast-overflow", "false");
1799
1800 // TODO: Are these all needed?
1801 // unsafe/inf/nan/nsz are handled by instruction-level FastMathFlags.
1802 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-infs-fp-math",
1803 llvm::toStringRef(LangOpts.NoHonorInfs));
1804 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-nans-fp-math",
1805 llvm::toStringRef(LangOpts.NoHonorNaNs));
1806 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("unsafe-fp-math",
1807 llvm::toStringRef(LangOpts.UnsafeFPMath));
1808 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("use-soft-float",
1809 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.SoftFloat));
1810 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stack-protector-buffer-size",
1811 llvm::utostr(CodeGenOpts.SSPBufferSize));
1812 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-signed-zeros-fp-math",
1813 llvm::toStringRef(LangOpts.NoSignedZero));
1814
1815 // TODO: Reciprocal estimate codegen options should apply to instructions?
1816 const std::vector<std::string> &Recips = CodeGenOpts.Reciprocals;
1817 if (!Recips.empty())
1818 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("reciprocal-estimates",
1819 llvm::join(Recips, ","));
1820
1821 if (!CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth.empty() &&
1822 CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth != "none")
1823 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("prefer-vector-width",
1824 CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth);
1825
1826 if (CodeGenOpts.StackRealignment)
1827 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stackrealign");
1828 if (CodeGenOpts.Backchain)
1829 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("backchain");
1830 if (CodeGenOpts.EnableSegmentedStacks)
1831 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("split-stack");
1832
1833 if (CodeGenOpts.SpeculativeLoadHardening)
1834 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
1835 }
1836
1837 if (getLangOpts().assumeFunctionsAreConvergent()) {
1838 // Conservatively, mark all functions and calls in CUDA and OpenCL as
1839 // convergent (meaning, they may call an intrinsically convergent op, such
1840 // as __syncthreads() / barrier(), and so can't have certain optimizations
1841 // applied around them). LLVM will remove this attribute where it safely
1842 // can.
1843 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
1844 }
1845
1846 if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1847 // Exceptions aren't supported in CUDA device code.
1848 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1849 }
1850
1851 for (StringRef Attr : CodeGenOpts.DefaultFunctionAttrs) {
1852 StringRef Var, Value;
1853 std::tie(Var, Value) = Attr.split('=');
1854 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(Var, Value);
1855 }
1856}
1857
1858void CodeGenModule::addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes(llvm::Function &F) {
1859 llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs;
1860 getDefaultFunctionAttributes(F.getName(), F.hasOptNone(),
1861 /* AttrOnCallSite = */ false, FuncAttrs);
1862 // TODO: call GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes?
1863 F.addAttributes(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, FuncAttrs);
1864}
1865
1866void CodeGenModule::addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes(
1867 llvm::AttrBuilder &attrs) {
1868 getDefaultFunctionAttributes(/*function name*/ "", /*optnone*/ false,
1869 /*for call*/ false, attrs);
1870 GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GlobalDecl(), attrs);
1871}
1872
1873static void addNoBuiltinAttributes(llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs,
1874 const LangOptions &LangOpts,
1875 const NoBuiltinAttr *NBA = nullptr) {
1876 auto AddNoBuiltinAttr = [&FuncAttrs](StringRef BuiltinName) {
1877 SmallString<32> AttributeName;
1878 AttributeName += "no-builtin-";
1879 AttributeName += BuiltinName;
1880 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(AttributeName);
1881 };
1882
1883 // First, handle the language options passed through -fno-builtin.
1884 if (LangOpts.NoBuiltin) {
1885 // -fno-builtin disables them all.
1886 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-builtins");
1887 return;
1888 }
1889
1890 // Then, add attributes for builtins specified through -fno-builtin-<name>.
1891 llvm::for_each(LangOpts.NoBuiltinFuncs, AddNoBuiltinAttr);
1892
1893 // Now, let's check the __attribute__((no_builtin("...")) attribute added to
1894 // the source.
1895 if (!NBA)
1896 return;
1897
1898 // If there is a wildcard in the builtin names specified through the
1899 // attribute, disable them all.
1900 if (llvm::is_contained(NBA->builtinNames(), "*")) {
1901 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-builtins");
1902 return;
1903 }
1904
1905 // And last, add the rest of the builtin names.
1906 llvm::for_each(NBA->builtinNames(), AddNoBuiltinAttr);
1907}
1908
1909/// Construct the IR attribute list of a function or call.
1910///
1911/// When adding an attribute, please consider where it should be handled:
1912///
1913/// - getDefaultFunctionAttributes is for attributes that are essentially
1914/// part of the global target configuration (but perhaps can be
1915/// overridden on a per-function basis). Adding attributes there
1916/// will cause them to also be set in frontends that build on Clang's
1917/// target-configuration logic, as well as for code defined in library
1918/// modules such as CUDA's libdevice.
1919///
1920/// - ConstructAttributeList builds on top of getDefaultFunctionAttributes
1921/// and adds declaration-specific, convention-specific, and
1922/// frontend-specific logic. The last is of particular importance:
1923/// attributes that restrict how the frontend generates code must be
1924/// added here rather than getDefaultFunctionAttributes.
1925///
1926void CodeGenModule::ConstructAttributeList(
1927 StringRef Name, const CGFunctionInfo &FI, CGCalleeInfo CalleeInfo,
1928 llvm::AttributeList &AttrList, unsigned &CallingConv, bool AttrOnCallSite) {
1929 llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs;
1930 llvm::AttrBuilder RetAttrs;
1931
1932 // Collect function IR attributes from the CC lowering.
1933 // We'll collect the paramete and result attributes later.
1934 CallingConv = FI.getEffectiveCallingConvention();
1935 if (FI.isNoReturn())
1936 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1937 if (FI.isCmseNSCall())
1938 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("cmse_nonsecure_call");
1939
1940 // Collect function IR attributes from the callee prototype if we have one.
1941 AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(getContext(), FuncAttrs,
1942 CalleeInfo.getCalleeFunctionProtoType());
1943
1944 const Decl *TargetDecl = CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
1945
1946 bool HasOptnone = false;
1947 // The NoBuiltinAttr attached to the target FunctionDecl.
1948 const NoBuiltinAttr *NBA = nullptr;
1949
1950 // Collect function IR attributes based on declaration-specific
1951 // information.
1952 // FIXME: handle sseregparm someday...
1953 if (TargetDecl) {
1954 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsTwiceAttr>())
1955 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReturnsTwice);
1956 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoThrowAttr>())
1957 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1958 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoReturnAttr>())
1959 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1960 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ColdAttr>())
1961 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Cold);
1962 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<HotAttr>())
1963 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Hot);
1964 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoDuplicateAttr>())
1965 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoDuplicate);
1966 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConvergentAttr>())
1967 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
1968
1969 if (const FunctionDecl *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
1970 AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(
1971 getContext(), FuncAttrs, Fn->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>());
1972 if (AttrOnCallSite && Fn->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
1973 // A sane operator new returns a non-aliasing pointer.
1974 auto Kind = Fn->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator();
1975 if (getCodeGenOpts().AssumeSaneOperatorNew &&
1976 (Kind == OO_New || Kind == OO_Array_New))
1977 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
1978 }
1979 const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn);
1980 const bool IsVirtualCall = MD && MD->isVirtual();
1981 // Don't use [[noreturn]], _Noreturn or [[no_builtin]] for a call to a
1982 // virtual function. These attributes are not inherited by overloads.
1983 if (!(AttrOnCallSite && IsVirtualCall)) {
1984 if (Fn->isNoReturn())
1985 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1986 NBA = Fn->getAttr<NoBuiltinAttr>();
1987 }
1988 // Only place nomerge attribute on call sites, never functions. This
1989 // allows it to work on indirect virtual function calls.
1990 if (AttrOnCallSite && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoMergeAttr>())
1991 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoMerge);
1992 }
1993
1994 // 'const', 'pure' and 'noalias' attributed functions are also nounwind.
1995 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConstAttr>()) {
1996 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
1997 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1998 // gcc specifies that 'const' functions have greater restrictions than
1999 // 'pure' functions, so they also cannot have infinite loops.
2000 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::WillReturn);
2001 } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<PureAttr>()) {
2002 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly);
2003 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2004 // gcc specifies that 'pure' functions cannot have infinite loops.
2005 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::WillReturn);
2006 } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoAliasAttr>()) {
2007 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ArgMemOnly);
2008 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2009 }
2010 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<RestrictAttr>())
2011 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2012 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>() &&
2013 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2014 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2015 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegistersAttr>())
2016 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no_caller_saved_registers");
2017 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCfCheckAttr>())
2018 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCfCheck);
2019 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<LeafAttr>())
2020 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCallback);
2021
2022 HasOptnone = TargetDecl->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>();
2023 if (auto *AllocSize = TargetDecl->getAttr<AllocSizeAttr>()) {
2024 Optional<unsigned> NumElemsParam;
2025 if (AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().isValid())
2026 NumElemsParam = AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().getLLVMIndex();
2027 FuncAttrs.addAllocSizeAttr(AllocSize->getElemSizeParam().getLLVMIndex(),
2028 NumElemsParam);
2029 }
2030
2031 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
2032 if (getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion <= 120) {
2033 // OpenCL v1.2 Work groups are always uniform
2034 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size", "true");
2035 } else {
2036 // OpenCL v2.0 Work groups may be whether uniform or not.
2037 // '-cl-uniform-work-group-size' compile option gets a hint
2038 // to the compiler that the global work-size be a multiple of
2039 // the work-group size specified to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel
2040 // (i.e. work groups are uniform).
2041 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size",
2042 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.UniformWGSize));
2043 }
2044 }
2045
2046 std::string AssumptionValueStr;
2047 for (AssumptionAttr *AssumptionA :
2048 TargetDecl->specific_attrs<AssumptionAttr>()) {
2049 std::string AS = AssumptionA->getAssumption().str();
2050 if (!AS.empty() && !AssumptionValueStr.empty())
2051 AssumptionValueStr += ",";
2052 AssumptionValueStr += AS;
2053 }
2054
2055 if (!AssumptionValueStr.empty())
2056 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::AssumptionAttrKey, AssumptionValueStr);
2057 }
2058
2059 // Attach "no-builtins" attributes to:
2060 // * call sites: both `nobuiltin` and "no-builtins" or "no-builtin-<name>".
2061 // * definitions: "no-builtins" or "no-builtin-<name>" only.
2062 // The attributes can come from:
2063 // * LangOpts: -ffreestanding, -fno-builtin, -fno-builtin-<name>
2064 // * FunctionDecl attributes: __attribute__((no_builtin(...)))
2065 addNoBuiltinAttributes(FuncAttrs, getLangOpts(), NBA);
2066
2067 // Collect function IR attributes based on global settiings.
2068 getDefaultFunctionAttributes(Name, HasOptnone, AttrOnCallSite, FuncAttrs);
2069
2070 // Override some default IR attributes based on declaration-specific
2071 // information.
2072 if (TargetDecl) {
2073 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
2074 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
2075 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<SpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
2076 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
2077 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSplitStackAttr>())
2078 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute("split-stack");
2079
2080 // Add NonLazyBind attribute to function declarations when -fno-plt
2081 // is used.
2082 // FIXME: what if we just haven't processed the function definition
2083 // yet, or if it's an external definition like C99 inline?
2084 if (CodeGenOpts.NoPLT) {
2085 if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
2086 if (!Fn->isDefined() && !AttrOnCallSite) {
2087 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind);
2088 }
2089 }
2090 }
2091 }
2092
2093 // Collect non-call-site function IR attributes from declaration-specific
2094 // information.
2095 if (!AttrOnCallSite) {
2096 if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<CmseNSEntryAttr>())
2097 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("cmse_nonsecure_entry");
2098
2099 // Whether tail calls are enabled.
2100 auto shouldDisableTailCalls = [&] {
2101 // Should this be honored in getDefaultFunctionAttributes?
2102 if (CodeGenOpts.DisableTailCalls)
2103 return true;
2104
2105 if (!TargetDecl)
2106 return false;
2107
2108 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<DisableTailCallsAttr>() ||
2109 TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86InterruptAttr>())
2110 return true;
2111
2112 if (CodeGenOpts.NoEscapingBlockTailCalls) {
2113 if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(TargetDecl))
2114 if (!BD->doesNotEscape())
2115 return true;
2116 }
2117
2118 return false;
2119 };
2120 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("disable-tail-calls",
2121 llvm::toStringRef(shouldDisableTailCalls()));
2122
2123 // CPU/feature overrides. addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes
2124 // handles these separately to set them based on the global defaults.
2125 GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl(), FuncAttrs);
2126 }
2127
2128 // Collect attributes from arguments and return values.
2129 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(getContext(), FI);
2130
2131 QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
2132 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
2133 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
2134 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2135 if (RetAI.isSignExt())
2136 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2137 else
2138 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2139 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2140 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2141 if (RetAI.getInReg())
2142 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2143 break;
2144 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2145 break;
2146
2147 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2148 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2149 // inalloca and sret disable readnone and readonly
2150 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2151 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2152 break;
2153 }
2154
2155 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2156 break;
2157
2158 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2159 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
2160 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
2161 }
2162
2163 if (const auto *RefTy = RetTy->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2164 QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2165 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2166 RetAttrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2167 getMinimumObjectSize(PTy).getQuantity());
2168 if (getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(PTy) == 0 &&
2169 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2170 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2171 if (PTy->isObjectType()) {
2172 llvm::Align Alignment =
2173 getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(RetTy).getAsAlign();
2174 RetAttrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2175 }
2176 }
2177
2178 bool hasUsedSRet = false;
2179 SmallVector<llvm::AttributeSet, 4> ArgAttrs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2180
2181 // Attach attributes to sret.
2182 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2183 llvm::AttrBuilder SRETAttrs;
2184 SRETAttrs.addStructRetAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(RetTy));
2185 hasUsedSRet = true;
2186 if (RetAI.getInReg())
2187 SRETAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2188 SRETAttrs.addAlignmentAttr(RetAI.getIndirectAlign().getQuantity());
2189 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] =
2190 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), SRETAttrs);
2191 }
2192
2193 // Attach attributes to inalloca argument.
2194 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2195 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2196 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InAlloca);
2197 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] =
2198 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2199 }
2200
2201 // Apply `nonnull` and `dereferencable(N)` to the `this` argument.
2202 if (FI.isInstanceMethod() && !IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg() &&
2203 !FI.arg_begin()->type->isVoidPointerType()) {
2204 auto IRArgs = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(0);
2205
2206 assert(IRArgs.second == 1 && "Expected only a single `this` pointer.");
2207
2208 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2209
2210 if (!CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid &&
2211 getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(FI.arg_begin()->type) == 0) {
2212 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2213 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2214 getMinimumObjectSize(
2215 FI.arg_begin()->type.castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType())
2216 .getQuantity());
2217 } else {
2218 // FIXME dereferenceable should be correct here, regardless of
2219 // NullPointerIsValid. However, dereferenceable currently does not always
2220 // respect NullPointerIsValid and may imply nonnull and break the program.
2221 // See https://reviews.llvm.org/D66618 for discussions.
2222 Attrs.addDereferenceableOrNullAttr(
2223 getMinimumObjectSize(
2224 FI.arg_begin()->type.castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType())
2225 .getQuantity());
2226 }
2227
2228 ArgAttrs[IRArgs.first] = llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2229 }
2230
2231 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2232 for (CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator I = FI.arg_begin(),
2233 E = FI.arg_end();
2234 I != E; ++I, ++ArgNo) {
2235 QualType ParamType = I->type;
2236 const ABIArgInfo &AI = I->info;
2237 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2238
2239 // Add attribute for padding argument, if necessary.
2240 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo)) {
2241 if (AI.getPaddingInReg()) {
2242 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
2243 llvm::AttributeSet::get(
2244 getLLVMContext(),
2245 llvm::AttrBuilder().addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg));
2246 }
2247 }
2248
2249 // 'restrict' -> 'noalias' is done in EmitFunctionProlog when we
2250 // have the corresponding parameter variable. It doesn't make
2251 // sense to do it here because parameters are so messed up.
2252 switch (AI.getKind()) {
2253 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2254 if (AI.isSignExt())
2255 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2256 else
2257 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2258 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2259 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2260 if (ArgNo == 0 && FI.isChainCall())
2261 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Nest);
2262 else if (AI.getInReg())
2263 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2264 break;
2265
2266 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2267 if (AI.getInReg())
2268 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2269
2270 if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2271 Attrs.addByValAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2272
2273 auto *Decl = ParamType->getAsRecordDecl();
2274 if (CodeGenOpts.PassByValueIsNoAlias && Decl &&
2275 Decl->getArgPassingRestrictions() == RecordDecl::APK_CanPassInRegs)
2276 // When calling the function, the pointer passed in will be the only
2277 // reference to the underlying object. Mark it accordingly.
2278 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2279
2280 // TODO: We could add the byref attribute if not byval, but it would
2281 // require updating many testcases.
2282
2283 CharUnits Align = AI.getIndirectAlign();
2284
2285 // In a byval argument, it is important that the required
2286 // alignment of the type is honored, as LLVM might be creating a
2287 // *new* stack object, and needs to know what alignment to give
2288 // it. (Sometimes it can deduce a sensible alignment on its own,
2289 // but not if clang decides it must emit a packed struct, or the
2290 // user specifies increased alignment requirements.)
2291 //
2292 // This is different from indirect *not* byval, where the object
2293 // exists already, and the align attribute is purely
2294 // informative.
2295 assert(!Align.isZero());
2296
2297 // For now, only add this when we have a byval argument.
2298 // TODO: be less lazy about updating test cases.
2299 if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2300 Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Align.getQuantity());
2301
2302 // byval disables readnone and readonly.
2303 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2304 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2305
2306 break;
2307 }
2308 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
2309 CharUnits Align = AI.getIndirectAlign();
2310 Attrs.addByRefAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2311 Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Align.getQuantity());
2312 break;
2313 }
2314 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2315 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2316 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2317 break;
2318
2319 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2320 // inalloca disables readnone and readonly.
2321 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2322 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2323 continue;
2324 }
2325
2326 if (const auto *RefTy = ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2327 QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2328 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2329 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2330 getMinimumObjectSize(PTy).getQuantity());
2331 if (getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(PTy) == 0 &&
2332 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2333 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2334 if (PTy->isObjectType()) {
2335 llvm::Align Alignment =
2336 getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(ParamType).getAsAlign();
2337 Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2338 }
2339 }
2340
2341 switch (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()) {
2342 case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2343 break;
2344
2345 case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult: {
2346 // Add 'sret' if we haven't already used it for something, but
2347 // only if the result is void.
2348 if (!hasUsedSRet && RetTy->isVoidType()) {
2349 Attrs.addStructRetAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2350 hasUsedSRet = true;
2351 }
2352
2353 // Add 'noalias' in either case.
2354 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2355
2356 // Add 'dereferenceable' and 'alignment'.
2357 auto PTy = ParamType->getPointeeType();
2358 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType()) {
2359 auto info = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(PTy);
2360 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(info.Width.getQuantity());
2361 Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(info.Align.getAsAlign());
2362 }
2363 break;
2364 }
2365
2366 case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2367 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftError);
2368 break;
2369
2370 case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2371 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftSelf);
2372 break;
2373 }
2374
2375 if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).isNoEscape())
2376 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCapture);
2377
2378 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) {
2379 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2380 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2381 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumIRArgs; i++)
2382 ArgAttrs[FirstIRArg + i] =
2383 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2384 }
2385 }
2386 assert(ArgNo == FI.arg_size());
2387
2388 AttrList = llvm::AttributeList::get(
2389 getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), FuncAttrs),
2390 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), RetAttrs), ArgAttrs);
2391}
2392
2393/// An argument came in as a promoted argument; demote it back to its
2394/// declared type.
2395static llvm::Value *emitArgumentDemotion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2396 const VarDecl *var,
2397 llvm::Value *value) {
2398 llvm::Type *varType = CGF.ConvertType(var->getType());
2399
2400 // This can happen with promotions that actually don't change the
2401 // underlying type, like the enum promotions.
2402 if (value->getType() == varType) return value;
2403
2404 assert((varType->isIntegerTy() || varType->isFloatingPointTy())
2405 && "unexpected promotion type");
2406
2407 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(varType))
2408 return CGF.Builder.CreateTrunc(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2409
2410 return CGF.Builder.CreateFPCast(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2411}
2412
2413/// Returns the attribute (either parameter attribute, or function
2414/// attribute), which declares argument ArgNo to be non-null.
2415static const NonNullAttr *getNonNullAttr(const Decl *FD, const ParmVarDecl *PVD,
2416 QualType ArgType, unsigned ArgNo) {
2417 // FIXME: __attribute__((nonnull)) can also be applied to:
2418 // - references to pointers, where the pointee is known to be
2419 // nonnull (apparently a Clang extension)
2420 // - transparent unions containing pointers
2421 // In the former case, LLVM IR cannot represent the constraint. In
2422 // the latter case, we have no guarantee that the transparent union
2423 // is in fact passed as a pointer.
2424 if (!ArgType->isAnyPointerType() && !ArgType->isBlockPointerType())
2425 return nullptr;
2426 // First, check attribute on parameter itself.
2427 if (PVD) {
2428 if (auto ParmNNAttr = PVD->getAttr<NonNullAttr>())
2429 return ParmNNAttr;
2430 }
2431 // Check function attributes.
2432 if (!FD)
2433 return nullptr;
2434 for (const auto *NNAttr : FD->specific_attrs<NonNullAttr>()) {
2435 if (NNAttr->isNonNull(ArgNo))
2436 return NNAttr;
2437 }
2438 return nullptr;
2439}
2440
2441namespace {
2442 struct CopyBackSwiftError final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
2443 Address Temp;
2444 Address Arg;
2445 CopyBackSwiftError(Address temp, Address arg) : Temp(temp), Arg(arg) {}
2446 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
2447 llvm::Value *errorValue = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Temp);
2448 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, Arg);
2449 }
2450 };
2451}
2452
2453void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionProlog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
2454 llvm::Function *Fn,
2455 const FunctionArgList &Args) {
2456 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
2457 // Naked functions don't have prologues.
2458 return;
2459
2460 // If this is an implicit-return-zero function, go ahead and
2461 // initialize the return value. TODO: it might be nice to have
2462 // a more general mechanism for this that didn't require synthesized
2463 // return statements.
2464 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
2465 if (FD->hasImplicitReturnZero()) {
2466 QualType RetTy = FD->getReturnType().getUnqualifiedType();
2467 llvm::Type* LLVMTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(RetTy);
2468 llvm::Constant* Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LLVMTy);
2469 Builder.CreateStore(Zero, ReturnValue);
2470 }
2471 }
2472
2473 // FIXME: We no longer need the types from FunctionArgList; lift up and
2474 // simplify.
2475
2476 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), FI);
2477 assert(Fn->arg_size() == IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2478
2479 // If we're using inalloca, all the memory arguments are GEPs off of the last
2480 // parameter, which is a pointer to the complete memory area.
2481 Address ArgStruct = Address::invalid();
2482 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2483 ArgStruct = Address(Fn->getArg(IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()),
2484 FI.getArgStructAlignment());
2485
2486 assert(ArgStruct.getType() == FI.getArgStruct()->getPointerTo());
2487 }
2488
2489 // Name the struct return parameter.
2490 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2491 auto AI = Fn->getArg(IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo());
2492 AI->setName("agg.result");
2493 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2494 }
2495
2496 // Track if we received the parameter as a pointer (indirect, byval, or
2497 // inalloca). If already have a pointer, EmitParmDecl doesn't need to copy it
2498 // into a local alloca for us.
2499 SmallVector<ParamValue, 16> ArgVals;
2500 ArgVals.reserve(Args.size());
2501
2502 // Create a pointer value for every parameter declaration. This usually
2503 // entails copying one or more LLVM IR arguments into an alloca. Don't push
2504 // any cleanups or do anything that might unwind. We do that separately, so
2505 // we can push the cleanups in the correct order for the ABI.
2506 assert(FI.arg_size() == Args.size() &&
2507 "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
2508 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2509 CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = FI.arg_begin();
2510 for (FunctionArgList::const_iterator i = Args.begin(), e = Args.end();
2511 i != e; ++i, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
2512 const VarDecl *Arg = *i;
2513 const ABIArgInfo &ArgI = info_it->info;
2514
2515 bool isPromoted =
2516 isa<ParmVarDecl>(Arg) && cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)->isKNRPromoted();
2517 // We are converting from ABIArgInfo type to VarDecl type directly, unless
2518 // the parameter is promoted. In this case we convert to
2519 // CGFunctionInfo::ArgInfo type with subsequent argument demotion.
2520 QualType Ty = isPromoted ? info_it->type : Arg->getType();
2521 assert(hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty) ==
2522 hasScalarEvaluationKind(Arg->getType()));
2523
2524 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2525 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2526
2527 switch (ArgI.getKind()) {
2528 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
2529 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
2530 auto FieldIndex = ArgI.getInAllocaFieldIndex();
2531 Address V =
2532 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgStruct, FieldIndex, Arg->getName());
2533 if (ArgI.getInAllocaIndirect())
2534 V = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(V),
2535 getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty));
2536 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2537 break;
2538 }
2539
2540 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
2541 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
2542 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2543 Address ParamAddr =
2544 Address(Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg), ArgI.getIndirectAlign());
2545
2546 if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2547 // Aggregates and complex variables are accessed by reference. All we
2548 // need to do is realign the value, if requested. Also, if the address
2549 // may be aliased, copy it to ensure that the parameter variable is
2550 // mutable and has a unique adress, as C requires.
2551 Address V = ParamAddr;
2552 if (ArgI.getIndirectRealign() || ArgI.isIndirectAliased()) {
2553 Address AlignedTemp = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "coerce");
2554
2555 // Copy from the incoming argument pointer to the temporary with the
2556 // appropriate alignment.
2557 //
2558 // FIXME: We should have a common utility for generating an aggregate
2559 // copy.
2560 CharUnits Size = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
2561 Builder.CreateMemCpy(
2562 AlignedTemp.getPointer(), AlignedTemp.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
2563 ParamAddr.getPointer(), ParamAddr.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
2564 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, Size.getQuantity()));
2565 V = AlignedTemp;
2566 }
2567 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2568 } else {
2569 // Load scalar value from indirect argument.
2570 llvm::Value *V =
2571 EmitLoadOfScalar(ParamAddr, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
2572
2573 if (isPromoted)
2574 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2575 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2576 }
2577 break;
2578 }
2579
2580 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2581 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
2582 auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
2583 llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertType(Arg->getType());
2584
2585 // Prepare parameter attributes. So far, only attributes for pointer
2586 // parameters are prepared. See
2587 // http://llvm.org/docs/LangRef.html#paramattrs.
2588 if (ArgI.getDirectOffset() == 0 && LTy->isPointerTy() &&
2589 ArgI.getCoerceToType()->isPointerTy()) {
2590 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2591
2592 if (const ParmVarDecl *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)) {
2593 // Set `nonnull` attribute if any.
2594 if (getNonNullAttr(CurCodeDecl, PVD, PVD->getType(),
2595 PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex()) &&
2596 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2597 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2598
2599 QualType OTy = PVD->getOriginalType();
2600 if (const auto *ArrTy =
2601 getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(OTy)) {
2602 // A C99 array parameter declaration with the static keyword also
2603 // indicates dereferenceability, and if the size is constant we can
2604 // use the dereferenceable attribute (which requires the size in
2605 // bytes).
2606 if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == ArrayType::Static) {
2607 QualType ETy = ArrTy->getElementType();
2608 llvm::Align Alignment =
2609 CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ETy).getAsAlign();
2610 AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder().addAlignmentAttr(Alignment));
2611 uint64_t ArrSize = ArrTy->getSize().getZExtValue();
2612 if (!ETy->isIncompleteType() && ETy->isConstantSizeType() &&
2613 ArrSize) {
2614 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2615 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2616 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ETy).getQuantity() *
2617 ArrSize);
2618 AI->addAttrs(Attrs);
2619 } else if (getContext().getTargetInfo().getNullPointerValue(
2620 ETy.getAddressSpace()) == 0 &&
2621 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid) {
2622 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2623 }
2624 }
2625 } else if (const auto *ArrTy =
2626 getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(OTy)) {
2627 // For C99 VLAs with the static keyword, we don't know the size so
2628 // we can't use the dereferenceable attribute, but in addrspace(0)
2629 // we know that it must be nonnull.
2630 if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == VariableArrayType::Static) {
2631 QualType ETy = ArrTy->getElementType();
2632 llvm::Align Alignment =
2633 CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ETy).getAsAlign();
2634 AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder().addAlignmentAttr(Alignment));
2635 if (!getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(ETy) &&
2636 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2637 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2638 }
2639 }
2640
2641 // Set `align` attribute if any.
2642 const auto *AVAttr = PVD->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2643 if (!AVAttr)
2644 if (const auto *TOTy = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(OTy))
2645 AVAttr = TOTy->getDecl()->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2646 if (AVAttr && !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
2647 // If alignment-assumption sanitizer is enabled, we do *not* add
2648 // alignment attribute here, but emit normal alignment assumption,
2649 // so the UBSAN check could function.
2650 llvm::ConstantInt *AlignmentCI =
2651 cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(EmitScalarExpr(AVAttr->getAlignment()));
2652 unsigned AlignmentInt =
2653 AlignmentCI->getLimitedValue(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment);
2654 if (AI->getParamAlign().valueOrOne() < AlignmentInt) {
2655 AI->removeAttr(llvm::Attribute::AttrKind::Alignment);
2656 AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder().addAlignmentAttr(
2657 llvm::Align(AlignmentInt)));
2658 }
2659 }
2660 }
2661
2662 // Set 'noalias' if an argument type has the `restrict` qualifier.
2663 if (Arg->getType().isRestrictQualified())
2664 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2665 }
2666
2667 // Prepare the argument value. If we have the trivial case, handle it
2668 // with no muss and fuss.
2669 if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType()) &&
2670 ArgI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(Ty) &&
2671 ArgI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
2672 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2673
2674 // LLVM expects swifterror parameters to be used in very restricted
2675 // ways. Copy the value into a less-restricted temporary.
2676 llvm::Value *V = AI;
2677 if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
2678 == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
2679 QualType pointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
2680 assert(pointeeTy->isPointerType());
2681 Address temp =
2682 CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
2683 Address arg = Address(V, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
2684 llvm::Value *incomingErrorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(arg);
2685 Builder.CreateStore(incomingErrorValue, temp);
2686 V = temp.getPointer();
2687
2688 // Push a cleanup to copy the value back at the end of the function.
2689 // The convention does not guarantee that the value will be written
2690 // back if the function exits with an unwind exception.
2691 EHStack.pushCleanup<CopyBackSwiftError>(NormalCleanup, temp, arg);
2692 }
2693
2694 // Ensure the argument is the correct type.
2695 if (V->getType() != ArgI.getCoerceToType())
2696 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2697
2698 if (isPromoted)
2699 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2700
2701 // Because of merging of function types from multiple decls it is
2702 // possible for the type of an argument to not match the corresponding
2703 // type in the function type. Since we are codegening the callee
2704 // in here, add a cast to the argument type.
2705 llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertType(Arg->getType());
2706 if (V->getType() != LTy)
2707 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, LTy);
2708
2709 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2710 break;
2711 }
2712
2713 // VLST arguments are coerced to VLATs at the function boundary for
2714 // ABI consistency. If this is a VLST that was coerced to
2715 // a VLAT at the function boundary and the types match up, use
2716 // llvm.experimental.vector.extract to convert back to the original
2717 // VLST.
2718 if (auto *VecTyTo = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ConvertType(Ty))) {
2719 auto *Coerced = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
2720 if (auto *VecTyFrom =
2721 dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Coerced->getType())) {
2722 if (VecTyFrom->getElementType() == VecTyTo->getElementType()) {
2723 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int64Ty);
2724
2725 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2726 Coerced->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce");
2727 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(Builder.CreateExtractVector(
2728 VecTyTo, Coerced, Zero, "castFixedSve")));
2729 break;
2730 }
2731 }
2732 }
2733
2734 Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg),
2735 Arg->getName());
2736
2737 // Pointer to store into.
2738 Address Ptr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Alloca, ArgI);
2739
2740 // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
2741 // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
2742 llvm::StructType *STy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2743 if (ArgI.isDirect() && ArgI.getCanBeFlattened() && STy &&
2744 STy->getNumElements() > 1) {
2745 uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
2746 llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr.getElementType();
2747 uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(DstTy);
2748
2749 Address AddrToStoreInto = Address::invalid();
2750 if (SrcSize <= DstSize) {
2751 AddrToStoreInto = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Ptr, STy);
2752 } else {
2753 AddrToStoreInto =
2754 CreateTempAlloca(STy, Alloca.getAlignment(), "coerce");
2755 }
2756
2757 assert(STy->getNumElements() == NumIRArgs);
2758 for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2759 auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg + i);
2760 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce" + Twine(i));
2761 Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(AddrToStoreInto, i);
2762 Builder.CreateStore(AI, EltPtr);
2763 }
2764
2765 if (SrcSize > DstSize) {
2766 Builder.CreateMemCpy(Ptr, AddrToStoreInto, DstSize);
2767 }
2768
2769 } else {
2770 // Simple case, just do a coerced store of the argument into the alloca.
2771 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2772 auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
2773 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce");
2774 CreateCoercedStore(AI, Ptr, /*DstIsVolatile=*/false, *this);
2775 }
2776
2777 // Match to what EmitParmDecl is expecting for this type.
2778 if (CodeGenFunction::hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2779 llvm::Value *V =
2780 EmitLoadOfScalar(Alloca, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
2781 if (isPromoted)
2782 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2783 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2784 } else {
2785 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
2786 }
2787 break;
2788 }
2789
2790 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
2791 // Reconstruct into a temporary.
2792 Address alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
2793 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(alloca));
2794
2795 auto coercionType = ArgI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
2796 alloca = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(alloca, coercionType);
2797
2798 unsigned argIndex = FirstIRArg;
2799 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2800 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
2801 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType))
2802 continue;
2803
2804 auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(alloca, i);
2805 auto elt = Fn->getArg(argIndex++);
2806 Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
2807 }
2808 assert(argIndex == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
2809 break;
2810 }
2811
2812 case ABIArgInfo::Expand: {
2813 // If this structure was expanded into multiple arguments then
2814 // we need to create a temporary and reconstruct it from the
2815 // arguments.
2816 Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
2817 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Alloca, Ty);
2818 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
2819
2820 auto FnArgIter = Fn->arg_begin() + FirstIRArg;
2821 ExpandTypeFromArgs(Ty, LV, FnArgIter);
2822 assert(FnArgIter == Fn->arg_begin() + FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
2823 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumIRArgs; i != e; ++i) {
2824 auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg + i);
2825 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + "." + Twine(i));
2826 }
2827 break;
2828 }
2829
2830 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2831 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
2832 // Initialize the local variable appropriately.
2833 if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2834 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(CreateMemTemp(Ty)));
2835 } else {
2836 llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Arg->getType()));
2837 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(U));
2838 }
2839 break;
2840 }
2841 }
2842
2843 if (getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()) {
2844 for (int I = Args.size() - 1; I >= 0; --I)
2845 EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
2846 } else {
2847 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I != E; ++I)
2848 EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
2849 }
2850}

2852static void eraseUnusedBitCasts(llvm::Instruction *insn) {
2853 while (insn->use_empty()) {
2854 llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(insn);
2855 if (!bitcast) return;
2856
2857 // This is "safe" because we would have used a ConstantExpr otherwise.
2858 insn = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
2859 bitcast->eraseFromParent();
2860 }
2861}
2862
2863/// Try to emit a fused autorelease of a return result.
2864static llvm::Value *tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2865 llvm::Value *result) {
2866 // We must be immediately followed the cast.
2867 llvm::BasicBlock *BB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2868 if (BB->empty()) return nullptr;
2869 if (&BB->back() != result) return nullptr;
2870
2871 llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
2872
2873 // result is in a BasicBlock and is therefore an Instruction.
2874 llvm::Instruction *generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(result);
2875
2876 SmallVector<llvm::Instruction *, 4> InstsToKill;
2877
2878 // Look for:
2879 // %generator = bitcast %type1* %generator2 to %type2*
2880 while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(generator)) {
2881 // We would have emitted this as a constant if the operand weren't
2882 // an Instruction.
2883 generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
2884
2885 // Require the generator to be immediately followed by the cast.
2886 if (generator->getNextNode() != bitcast)
2887 return nullptr;
2888
2889 InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
2890 }
2891
2892 // Look for:
2893 // %generator = call i8* @objc_retain(i8* %originalResult)
2894 // or
2895 // %generator = call i8* @objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue(i8* %originalResult)
2896 llvm::CallInst *call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(generator);
2897 if (!call) return nullptr;
2898
2899 bool doRetainAutorelease;
2900
2901 if (call->getCalledOperand() == CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain) {
2902 doRetainAutorelease = true;
2903 } else if (call->getCalledOperand() ==
2904 CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue) {
2905 doRetainAutorelease = false;
2906
2907 // If we emitted an assembly marker for this call (and the
2908 // ARCEntrypoints field should have been set if so), go looking
2909 // for that call. If we can't find it, we can't do this
2910 // optimization. But it should always be the immediately previous
2911 // instruction, unless we needed bitcasts around the call.
2912 if (CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker) {
2913 llvm::Instruction *prev = call->getPrevNode();
2914 assert(prev);
2915 if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(prev)) {
2916 prev = prev->getPrevNode();
2917 assert(prev);
2918 }
2919 assert(isa<llvm::CallInst>(prev));
2920 assert(cast<llvm::CallInst>(prev)->getCalledOperand() ==
2921 CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker);
2922 InstsToKill.push_back(prev);
2923 }
2924 } else {
2925 return nullptr;
2926 }
2927
2928 result = call->getArgOperand(0);
2929 InstsToKill.push_back(call);
2930
2931 // Keep killing bitcasts, for sanity. Note that we no longer care
2932 // about precise ordering as long as there's exactly one use.
2933 while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(result)) {
2934 if (!bitcast->hasOneUse()) break;
2935 InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
2936 result = bitcast->getOperand(0);
2937 }
2938
2939 // Delete all the unnecessary instructions, from latest to earliest.
2940 for (auto *I : InstsToKill)
2941 I->eraseFromParent();
2942
2943 // Do the fused retain/autorelease if we were asked to.
2944 if (doRetainAutorelease)
2945 result = CGF.EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
2946
2947 // Cast back to the result type.
2948 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, resultType);
2949}
2950
2951/// If this is a +1 of the value of an immutable 'self', remove it.
2952static llvm::Value *tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2953 llvm::Value *result) {
2954 // This is only applicable to a method with an immutable 'self'.
2955 const ObjCMethodDecl *method =
2956 dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
2957 if (!method) return nullptr;
2958 const VarDecl *self = method->getSelfDecl();
2959 if (!self->getType().isConstQualified()) return nullptr;
2960
2961 // Look for a retain call.
2962 llvm::CallInst *retainCall =
2963 dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(result->stripPointerCasts());
2964 if (!retainCall || retainCall->getCalledOperand() !=
2965 CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain)
2966 return nullptr;
2967
2968 // Look for an ordinary load of 'self'.
2969 llvm::Value *retainedValue = retainCall->getArgOperand(0);
2970 llvm::LoadInst *load =
2971 dyn_cast<llvm::LoadInst>(retainedValue->stripPointerCasts());
2972 if (!load || load->isAtomic() || load->isVolatile() ||
2973 load->getPointerOperand() != CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(self).getPointer())
2974 return nullptr;
2975
2976 // Okay! Burn it all down. This relies for correctness on the
2977 // assumption that the retain is emitted as part of the return and
2978 // that thereafter everything is used "linearly".
2979 llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
2980 eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(result));
2981 assert(retainCall->use_empty());
2982 retainCall->eraseFromParent();
2983 eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(retainedValue));
2984
2985 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(load, resultType);
2986}

2988/// Emit an ARC autorelease of the result of a function.
2989///
2990/// \return the value to actually return from the function
2991static llvm::Value *emitAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2992 llvm::Value *result) {
2993 // If we're returning 'self', kill the initial retain. This is a
2994 // heuristic attempt to "encourage correctness" in the really unfortunate
2995 // case where we have a return of self during a dealloc and we desperately
2996 // need to avoid the possible autorelease.
2997 if (llvm::Value *self = tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CGF, result))
2998 return self;
2999
3000 // At -O0, try to emit a fused retain/autorelease.
3001 if (CGF.shouldUseFusedARCCalls())
3002 if (llvm::Value *fused = tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CGF, result))
3003 return fused;
3004
3005 return CGF.EmitARCAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
3006}

3008/// Heuristically search for a dominating store to the return-value slot.
3009static llvm::StoreInst *findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
3010 // Check if a User is a store which pointerOperand is the ReturnValue.
3011 // We are looking for stores to the ReturnValue, not for stores of the
3012 // ReturnValue to some other location.
3013 auto GetStoreIfValid = [&CGF](llvm::User *U) -> llvm::StoreInst * {
3014 auto *SI = dyn_cast<llvm::StoreInst>(U);
3015 if (!SI || SI->getPointerOperand() != CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer())
3016 return nullptr;
3017 // These aren't actually possible for non-coerced returns, and we
3018 // only care about non-coerced returns on this code path.
3019 assert(!SI->isAtomic() && !SI->isVolatile());
3020 return SI;
3021 };
3022 // If there are multiple uses of the return-value slot, just check
3023 // for something immediately preceding the IP. Sometimes this can
3024 // happen with how we generate implicit-returns; it can also happen
3025 // with noreturn cleanups.
3026 if (!CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->hasOneUse()) {
3027 llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3028 if (IP->empty()) return nullptr;
3029 llvm::Instruction *I = &IP->back();
3030
3031 // Skip lifetime markers
3032 for (llvm::BasicBlock::reverse_iterator II = IP->rbegin(),
3033 IE = IP->rend();
3034 II != IE; ++II) {
3035 if (llvm::IntrinsicInst *Intrinsic =
3036 dyn_cast<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(&*II)) {
3037 if (Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID() == llvm::Intrinsic::lifetime_end) {
3038 const llvm::Value *CastAddr = Intrinsic->getArgOperand(1);
3039 ++II;
3040 if (II == IE)
3041 break;
3042 if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(&*II) && (CastAddr == &*II))
3043 continue;
3044 }
3045 }
3046 I = &*II;
3047 break;
3048 }
3049
3050 return GetStoreIfValid(I);
3051 }
3052
3053 llvm::StoreInst *store =
3054 GetStoreIfValid(CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->user_back());
3055 if (!store) return nullptr;
3056
3057 // Now do a first-and-dirty dominance check: just walk up the
3058 // single-predecessors chain from the current insertion point.
3059 llvm::BasicBlock *StoreBB = store->getParent();
3060 llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3061 while (IP != StoreBB) {
3062 if (!(IP = IP->getSinglePredecessor()))
3063 return nullptr;
3064 }
3065
3066 // Okay, the store's basic block dominates the insertion point; we
3067 // can do our thing.
3068 return store;
3069}

3071// Helper functions for EmitCMSEClearRecord
3072
3073// Set the bits corresponding to a field having width `BitWidth` and located at
3074// offset `BitOffset` (from the least significant bit) within a storage unit of
3075// `Bits.size()` bytes. Each element of `Bits` corresponds to one target byte.
3076// Use little-endian layout, i.e.`Bits[0]` is the LSB.
3077static void setBitRange(SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits, int BitOffset,
3078 int BitWidth, int CharWidth) {
3079 assert(CharWidth <= 64);
3080 assert(static_cast<unsigned>(BitWidth) <= Bits.size() * CharWidth);
3081
3082 int Pos = 0;
3083 if (BitOffset >= CharWidth) {
3084 Pos += BitOffset / CharWidth;
3085 BitOffset = BitOffset % CharWidth;
3086 }
3087
3088 const uint64_t Used = (uint64_t(1) << CharWidth) - 1;
3089 if (BitOffset + BitWidth >= CharWidth) {
3090 Bits[Pos++] |= (Used << BitOffset) & Used;
3091 BitWidth -= CharWidth - BitOffset;
3092 BitOffset = 0;
3093 }
3094
3095 while (BitWidth >= CharWidth) {
3096 Bits[Pos++] = Used;
3097 BitWidth -= CharWidth;
3098 }
3099
3100 if (BitWidth > 0)
3101 Bits[Pos++] |= (Used >> (CharWidth - BitWidth)) << BitOffset;
3102}
3103
3104// Set the bits corresponding to a field having width `BitWidth` and located at
3105// offset `BitOffset` (from the least significant bit) within a storage unit of
3106// `StorageSize` bytes, located at `StorageOffset` in `Bits`. Each element of
3107// `Bits` corresponds to one target byte. Use target endian layout.
3108static void setBitRange(SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits, int StorageOffset,
3109 int StorageSize, int BitOffset, int BitWidth,
3110 int CharWidth, bool BigEndian) {
3111
3112 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> TmpBits(StorageSize);
3113 setBitRange(TmpBits, BitOffset, BitWidth, CharWidth);
3114
3115 if (BigEndian)
3116 std::reverse(TmpBits.begin(), TmpBits.end());
3117
3118 for (uint64_t V : TmpBits)
3119 Bits[StorageOffset++] |= V;
3120}
3121
3122static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &, QualType, int,
3123 SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &);
3124
3125// Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3126// the actual members of the record type `RTy`. Note that this function does
3127// not handle base classes, virtual tables, etc, since they cannot happen in
3128// CMSE function arguments or return. The bit mask corresponds to the target
3129// memory layout, i.e. it's endian dependent.
3130static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, const RecordType *RTy, int Offset,
3131 SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3132 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3133 int CharWidth = Context.getCharWidth();
3134 const RecordDecl *RD = RTy->getDecl()->getDefinition();
3135 const ASTRecordLayout &ASTLayout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3136 const CGRecordLayout &Layout = CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD);
3137
3138 int Idx = 0;
3139 for (auto I = RD->field_begin(), E = RD->field_end(); I != E; ++I, ++Idx) {
3140 const FieldDecl *F = *I;
3141
3142 if (F->isUnnamedBitfield() || F->isZeroLengthBitField(Context) ||
3143 F->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType())
3144 continue;
3145
3146 if (F->isBitField()) {
3147 const CGBitFieldInfo &BFI = Layout.getBitFieldInfo(F);
3148 setBitRange(Bits, Offset + BFI.StorageOffset.getQuantity(),
3149 BFI.StorageSize / CharWidth, BFI.Offset,
3150 BFI.Size, CharWidth,
3151 CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian());
3152 continue;
3153 }
3154
3155 setUsedBits(CGM, F->getType(),
3156 Offset + ASTLayout.getFieldOffset(Idx) / CharWidth, Bits);
3157 }
3158}
3159
3160// Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3161// the elements of an array type `ATy`.
3162static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, const ConstantArrayType *ATy,
3163 int Offset, SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3164 const ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3165
3166 QualType ETy = Context.getBaseElementType(ATy);
3167 int Size = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(ETy).getQuantity();
3168 SmallVector<uint64_t, 4> TmpBits(Size);
3169 setUsedBits(CGM, ETy, 0, TmpBits);
3170
3171 for (int I = 0, N = Context.getConstantArrayElementCount(ATy); I < N; ++I) {
3172 auto Src = TmpBits.begin();
3173 auto Dst = Bits.begin() + Offset + I * Size;
3174 for (int J = 0; J < Size; ++J)
3175 *Dst++ |= *Src++;
3176 }
3177}
3178
3179// Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3180// the type `QTy`.
3181static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, QualType QTy, int Offset,
3182 SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3183 if (const auto *RTy = QTy->getAs<RecordType>())
3184 return setUsedBits(CGM, RTy, Offset, Bits);
3185
3186 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3187 if (const auto *ATy = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(QTy))
3188 return setUsedBits(CGM, ATy, Offset, Bits);
3189
3190 int Size = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(QTy).getQuantity();
3191 if (Size <= 0)
3192 return;
3193
3194 std::fill_n(Bits.begin() + Offset, Size,
3195 (uint64_t(1) << Context.getCharWidth()) - 1);
3196}
3197
3198static uint64_t buildMultiCharMask(const SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits,
3199 int Pos, int Size, int CharWidth,
3200 bool BigEndian) {
3201 assert(Size > 0);
3202 uint64_t Mask = 0;
3203 if (BigEndian) {
3204 for (auto P = Bits.begin() + Pos, E = Bits.begin() + Pos + Size; P != E;
3205 ++P)
3206 Mask = (Mask << CharWidth) | *P;
3207 } else {
3208 auto P = Bits.begin() + Pos + Size, End = Bits.begin() + Pos;
3209 do
3210 Mask = (Mask << CharWidth) | *--P;
3211 while (P != End);
3212 }
3213 return Mask;
3214}

3216// Emit code to clear the bits in a record, which aren't a part of any user
3217// declared member, when the record is a function return.
3218llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCMSEClearRecord(llvm::Value *Src,
3219 llvm::IntegerType *ITy,
3220 QualType QTy) {
3221 assert(Src->getType() == ITy);
3222 assert(ITy->getScalarSizeInBits() <= 64);
3223
3224 const llvm::DataLayout &DataLayout = CGM.getDataLayout();
3225 int Size = DataLayout.getTypeStoreSize(ITy);
3226 SmallVector<uint64_t, 4> Bits(Size);
3227 setUsedBits(CGM, QTy->castAs<RecordType>(), 0, Bits);
3228
3229 int CharWidth = CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
3230 uint64_t Mask =
3231 buildMultiCharMask(Bits, 0, Size, CharWidth, DataLayout.isBigEndian());
3232
3233 return Builder.CreateAnd(Src, Mask, "cmse.clear");
3234}
3235
3236// Emit code to clear the bits in a record, which aren't a part of any user
3237// declared member, when the record is a function argument.
3238llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCMSEClearRecord(llvm::Value *Src,
3239 llvm::ArrayType *ATy,
3240 QualType QTy) {
3241 const llvm::DataLayout &DataLayout = CGM.getDataLayout();
3242 int Size = DataLayout.getTypeStoreSize(ATy);
3243 SmallVector<uint64_t, 16> Bits(Size);
3244 setUsedBits(CGM, QTy->castAs<RecordType>(), 0, Bits);
3245
3246 // Clear each element of the LLVM array.
3247 int CharWidth = CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
3248 int CharsPerElt =
3249 ATy->getArrayElementType()->getScalarSizeInBits() / CharWidth;
3250 int MaskIndex = 0;
3251 llvm::Value *R = llvm::UndefValue::get(ATy);
3252 for (int I = 0, N = ATy->getArrayNumElements(); I != N; ++I) {
3253 uint64_t Mask = buildMultiCharMask(Bits, MaskIndex, CharsPerElt, CharWidth,
3254 DataLayout.isBigEndian());
3255 MaskIndex += CharsPerElt;
3256 llvm::Value *T0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I);
3257 llvm::Value *T1 = Builder.CreateAnd(T0, Mask, "cmse.clear");
3258 R = Builder.CreateInsertValue(R, T1, I);
3259 }
3260
3261 return R;
3262}

3264void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionEpilog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
3265 bool EmitRetDbgLoc,
3266 SourceLocation EndLoc) {
3267 if (FI.isNoReturn()) {
3268 // Noreturn functions don't return.
3269 EmitUnreachable(EndLoc);
3270 return;
3271 }
3272
3273 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>()) {
3274 // Naked functions don't have epilogues.
3275 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3276 return;
3277 }
3278
3279 // Functions with no result always return void.
3280 if (!ReturnValue.isValid()) {
3281 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3282 return;
3283 }
3284
3285 llvm::DebugLoc RetDbgLoc;
3286 llvm::Value *RV = nullptr;
3287 QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
3288 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
3289
3290 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
3291 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
3292 // Aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination. Sometimes we
3293 // need to return the sret value in a register, though.
3294 assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(RetTy));
3295 if (RetAI.getInAllocaSRet()) {
3296 llvm::Function::arg_iterator EI = CurFn->arg_end();
3297 --EI;
3298 llvm::Value *ArgStruct = &*EI;
3299 llvm::Value *SRet = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
3300 nullptr, ArgStruct, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
3301 RV = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(SRet, getPointerAlign(), "sret");
3302 }
3303 break;
3304
3305 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
3306 auto AI = CurFn->arg_begin();
3307 if (RetAI.isSRetAfterThis())
3308 ++AI;
3309 switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
3310 case TEK_Complex: {
3311 ComplexPairTy RT =
3312 EmitLoadOfComplex(MakeAddrLValue(ReturnValue, RetTy), EndLoc);
3313 EmitStoreOfComplex(RT, MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(&*AI, RetTy),
3314 /*isInit*/ true);
3315 break;
3316 }
3317 case TEK_Aggregate:
3318 // Do nothing; aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination.
3319 break;
3320 case TEK_Scalar:
3321 EmitStoreOfScalar(Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue),
3322 MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(&*AI, RetTy),
3323 /*isInit*/ true);
3324 break;
3325 }
3326 break;
3327 }
3328
3329 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
3330 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
3331 if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(RetTy) &&
3332 RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
3333 // The internal return value temp always will have pointer-to-return-type
3334 // type, just do a load.
3335
3336 // If there is a dominating store to ReturnValue, we can elide
3337 // the load, zap the store, and usually zap the alloca.
3338 if (llvm::StoreInst *SI =
3339 findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(*this)) {
3340 // Reuse the debug location from the store unless there is
3341 // cleanup code to be emitted between the store and return
3342 // instruction.
3343 if (EmitRetDbgLoc && !AutoreleaseResult)
3344 RetDbgLoc = SI->getDebugLoc();
3345 // Get the stored value and nuke the now-dead store.
3346 RV = SI->getValueOperand();
3347 SI->eraseFromParent();
3348
3349 // Otherwise, we have to do a simple load.
3350 } else {
3351 RV = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue);
3352 }
3353 } else {
3354 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
3355 Address V = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, ReturnValue, RetAI);
3356
3357 RV = CreateCoercedLoad(V, RetAI.getCoerceToType(), *this);
3358 }
3359
3360 // In ARC, end functions that return a retainable type with a call
3361 // to objc_autoreleaseReturnValue.
3362 if (AutoreleaseResult) {
3363#ifndef NDEBUG
3364 // Type::isObjCRetainabletype has to be called on a QualType that hasn't
3365 // been stripped of the typedefs, so we cannot use RetTy here. Get the
3366 // original return type of FunctionDecl, CurCodeDecl, and BlockDecl from
3367 // CurCodeDecl or BlockInfo.
3368 QualType RT;
3369
3370 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3371 RT = FD->getReturnType();
3372 else if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3373 RT = MD->getReturnType();
3374 else if (isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3375 RT = BlockInfo->BlockExpression->getFunctionType()->getReturnType();
3376 else
3377 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected function/method type");
3378
3379 assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
3380 !FI.isReturnsRetained() &&
3381 RT->isObjCRetainableType());
3382#endif
3383 RV = emitAutoreleaseOfResult(*this, RV);
3384 }
3385
3386 break;
3387
3388 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
3389 break;
3390
3391 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
3392 auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
3393
3394 // Load all of the coerced elements out into results.
3395 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 4> results;
3396 Address addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(ReturnValue, coercionType);
3397 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
3398 auto coercedEltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
3399 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(coercedEltType))
3400 continue;
3401
3402 auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
3403 auto elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
3404 results.push_back(elt);
3405 }
3406
3407 // If we have one result, it's the single direct result type.
3408 if (results.size() == 1) {
3409 RV = results[0];
3410
3411 // Otherwise, we need to make a first-class aggregate.
3412 } else {
3413 // Construct a return type that lacks padding elements.
3414 llvm::Type *returnType = RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType();
3415
3416 RV = llvm::UndefValue::get(returnType);
3417 for (unsigned i = 0, e = results.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3418 RV = Builder.CreateInsertValue(RV, results[i], i);
3419 }
3420 }
3421 break;
3422 }
3423 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
3424 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
3425 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
3426 }
3427
3428 llvm::Instruction *Ret;
3429 if (RV) {
3430 if (CurFuncDecl && CurFuncDecl->hasAttr<CmseNSEntryAttr>()) {
3431 // For certain return types, clear padding bits, as they may reveal
3432 // sensitive information.
3433 // Small struct/union types are passed as integers.
3434 auto *ITy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(RV->getType());
3435 if (ITy != nullptr && isa<RecordType>(RetTy.getCanonicalType()))
3436 RV = EmitCMSEClearRecord(RV, ITy, RetTy);
3437 }
3438 EmitReturnValueCheck(RV);
3439 Ret = Builder.CreateRet(RV);
3440 } else {
3441 Ret = Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3442 }
3443
3444 if (RetDbgLoc)
3445 Ret->setDebugLoc(std::move(RetDbgLoc));
3446}

3448void CodeGenFunction::EmitReturnValueCheck(llvm::Value *RV) {
3449 // A current decl may not be available when emitting vtable thunks.
3450 if (!CurCodeDecl)
3451 return;
3452
3453 // If the return block isn't reachable, neither is this check, so don't emit
3454 // it.
3455 if (ReturnBlock.isValid() && ReturnBlock.getBlock()->use_empty())
3456 return;
3457
3458 ReturnsNonNullAttr *RetNNAttr = nullptr;
3459 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute))
3460 RetNNAttr = CurCodeDecl->getAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>();
3461
3462 if (!RetNNAttr && !requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3463 return;
3464
3465 // Prefer the returns_nonnull attribute if it's present.
3466 SourceLocation AttrLoc;
3467 SanitizerMask CheckKind;
3468 SanitizerHandler Handler;
3469 if (RetNNAttr) {
3470 assert(!requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck() &&
3471 "Cannot check nullability and the nonnull attribute");
3472 AttrLoc = RetNNAttr->getLocation();
3473 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute;
3474 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullReturn;
3475 } else {
3476 if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3477 if (auto *TSI = DD->getTypeSourceInfo())
3478 if (auto FTL = TSI->getTypeLoc().getAsAdjusted<FunctionTypeLoc>())
3479 AttrLoc = FTL.getReturnLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
3480 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityReturn;
3481 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityReturn;
3482 }
3483
3484 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3485
3486 // Make sure the "return" source location is valid. If we're checking a
3487 // nullability annotation, make sure the preconditions for the check are met.
3488 llvm::BasicBlock *Check = createBasicBlock("nullcheck");
3489 llvm::BasicBlock *NoCheck = createBasicBlock("no.nullcheck");
3490 llvm::Value *SLocPtr = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnLocation, "return.sloc.load");
3491 llvm::Value *CanNullCheck = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(SLocPtr);
3492 if (requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3493 CanNullCheck =
3494 Builder.CreateAnd(CanNullCheck, RetValNullabilityPrecondition);
3495 Builder.CreateCondBr(CanNullCheck, Check, NoCheck);
3496 EmitBlock(Check);
3497
3498 // Now do the null check.
3499 llvm::Value *Cond = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(RV);
3500 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc)};
3501 llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = {SLocPtr};
3502 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, DynamicData);
3503
3504 EmitBlock(NoCheck);
3505
3506#ifndef NDEBUG
3507 // The return location should not be used after the check has been emitted.
3508 ReturnLocation = Address::invalid();
3509#endif
3510}

3538void CodeGenFunction::EmitDelegateCallArg(CallArgList &args,
3539 const VarDecl *param,
3540 SourceLocation loc) {
3541 // StartFunction converted the ABI-lowered parameter(s) into a
3542 // local alloca. We need to turn that into an r-value suitable
3543 // for EmitCall.
3544 Address local = GetAddrOfLocalVar(param);
3545
3546 QualType type = param->getType();
3547
3548 if (isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), type)) {
3549 CGM.ErrorUnsupported(param, "forwarded non-trivially copyable parameter");
3550 }
3551
3552 // GetAddrOfLocalVar returns a pointer-to-pointer for references,
3553 // but the argument needs to be the original pointer.
3554 if (type->isReferenceType()) {
3555 args.add(RValue::get(Builder.CreateLoad(local)), type);
3556
3557 // In ARC, move out of consumed arguments so that the release cleanup
3558 // entered by StartFunction doesn't cause an over-release. This isn't
3559 // optimal -O0 code generation, but it should get cleaned up when
3560 // optimization is enabled. This also assumes that delegate calls are
3561 // performed exactly once for a set of arguments, but that should be safe.
3562 } else if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
3563 param->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>() &&
3564 type->isObjCRetainableType()) {
3565 llvm::Value *ptr = Builder.CreateLoad(local);
3566 auto null =
3567 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ptr->getType()));
3568 Builder.CreateStore(null, local);
3569 args.add(RValue::get(ptr), type);
3570
3571 // For the most part, we just need to load the alloca, except that
3572 // aggregate r-values are actually pointers to temporaries.
3573 } else {
3574 args.add(convertTempToRValue(local, type, loc), type);
3575 }
3576
3577 // Deactivate the cleanup for the callee-destructed param that was pushed.
3578 if (hasAggregateEvaluationKind(type) && !CurFuncIsThunk &&
3579 type->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee() &&
3580 param->needsDestruction(getContext())) {
3581 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator cleanup =
3582 CalleeDestructedParamCleanups.lookup(cast<ParmVarDecl>(param));
3583 assert(cleanup.isValid() &&
3584 "cleanup for callee-destructed param not recorded");
3585 // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
3586 llvm::Instruction *isActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3587 args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(cleanup, isActive);
3588 }
3589}

3591static bool isProvablyNull(llvm::Value *addr) {
3592 return isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(addr);
3593}
3594
3595/// Emit the actual writing-back of a writeback.
3596static void emitWriteback(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3597 const CallArgList::Writeback &writeback) {
3598 const LValue &srcLV = writeback.Source;
3599 Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress(CGF);
3600 assert(!isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer()) &&
3601 "shouldn't have writeback for provably null argument");
3602
3603 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3604
3605 // If the argument wasn't provably non-null, we need to null check
3606 // before doing the store.
3607 bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3608 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3609 if (!provablyNonNull) {
3610 llvm::BasicBlock *writebackBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.writeback");
3611 contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.done");
3612
3613 llvm::Value *isNull =
3614 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
3615 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, writebackBB);
3616 CGF.EmitBlock(writebackBB);
3617 }
3618
3619 // Load the value to writeback.
3620 llvm::Value *value = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(writeback.Temporary);
3621
3622 // Cast it back, in case we're writing an id to a Foo* or something.
3623 value = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(value, srcAddr.getElementType(),
3624 "icr.writeback-cast");
3625
3626 // Perform the writeback.
3627
3628 // If we have a "to use" value, it's something we need to emit a use
3629 // of. This has to be carefully threaded in: if it's done after the
3630 // release it's potentially undefined behavior (and the optimizer
3631 // will ignore it), and if it happens before the retain then the
3632 // optimizer could move the release there.
3633 if (writeback.ToUse) {
3634 assert(srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong);
3635
3636 // Retain the new value. No need to block-copy here: the block's
3637 // being passed up the stack.
3638 value = CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(value);
3639
3640 // Emit the intrinsic use here.
3641 CGF.EmitARCIntrinsicUse(writeback.ToUse);
3642
3643 // Load the old value (primitively).
3644 llvm::Value *oldValue = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(srcLV, SourceLocation());
3645
3646 // Put the new value in place (primitively).
3647 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(value, srcLV, /*init*/ false);
3648
3649 // Release the old value.
3650 CGF.EmitARCRelease(oldValue, srcLV.isARCPreciseLifetime());
3651
3652 // Otherwise, we can just do a normal lvalue store.
3653 } else {
3654 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), srcLV);
3655 }
3656
3657 // Jump to the continuation block.
3658 if (!provablyNonNull)
3659 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
3660}
3661
3662static void emitWritebacks(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3663 const CallArgList &args) {
3664 for (const auto &I : args.writebacks())
3665 emitWriteback(CGF, I);
3666}

3668static void deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3669 const CallArgList &CallArgs) {
3670 ArrayRef<CallArgList::CallArgCleanup> Cleanups =
3671 CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate();
3672 // Iterate in reverse to increase the likelihood of popping the cleanup.
3673 for (const auto &I : llvm::reverse(Cleanups)) {
3674 CGF.DeactivateCleanupBlock(I.Cleanup, I.IsActiveIP);
3675 I.IsActiveIP->eraseFromParent();
3676 }
3677}

3679static const Expr *maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(const Expr *E) {
3680 if (const UnaryOperator *uop = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E->IgnoreParens()))
3681 if (uop->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
3682 return uop->getSubExpr();
3683 return nullptr;
3684}
