3686/// Emit an argument that's being passed call-by-writeback. That is,
3687/// we are passing the address of an __autoreleased temporary; it
3688/// might be copy-initialized with the current value of the given
3689/// address, but it will definitely be copied out of after the call.
3690static void emitWritebackArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, CallArgList &args,
3691 const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE) {
3692 LValue srcLV;
3693
3694 // Make an optimistic effort to emit the address as an l-value.
3695 // This can fail if the argument expression is more complicated.
3696 if (const Expr *lvExpr = maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(CRE->getSubExpr())) {
3697 srcLV = CGF.EmitLValue(lvExpr);
3698
3699 // Otherwise, just emit it as a scalar.
3700 } else {
3701 Address srcAddr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CRE->getSubExpr());
3702
3703 QualType srcAddrType =
3704 CRE->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3705 srcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(srcAddr, srcAddrType);
3706 }
3707 Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress(CGF);
3708
3709 // The dest and src types don't necessarily match in LLVM terms
3710 // because of the crazy ObjC compatibility rules.
3711
3712 llvm::PointerType *destType =
3713 cast<llvm::PointerType>(CGF.ConvertType(CRE->getType()));
3714
3715 // If the address is a constant null, just pass the appropriate null.
3716 if (isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer())) {
3717 args.add(RValue::get(llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType)),
3718 CRE->getType());
3719 return;
3720 }
3721
3722 // Create the temporary.
3723 Address temp = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(destType->getElementType(),
3724 CGF.getPointerAlign(),
3725 "icr.temp");
3726 // Loading an l-value can introduce a cleanup if the l-value is __weak,
3727 // and that cleanup will be conditional if we can't prove that the l-value
3728 // isn't null, so we need to register a dominating point so that the cleanups
3729 // system will make valid IR.
3730 CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation condEval(CGF);
3731
3732 // Zero-initialize it if we're not doing a copy-initialization.
3733 bool shouldCopy = CRE->shouldCopy();
3734 if (!shouldCopy) {
3735 llvm::Value *null =
3736 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(
3737 cast<llvm::PointerType>(destType->getElementType()));
3738 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(null, temp);
3739 }
3740
3741 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3742 llvm::BasicBlock *originBB = nullptr;
3743
3744 // If the address is *not* known to be non-null, we need to switch.
3745 llvm::Value *finalArgument;
3746
3747 bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3748 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3749 if (provablyNonNull) {
3750 finalArgument = temp.getPointer();
3751 } else {
3752 llvm::Value *isNull =
3753 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
3754
3755 finalArgument = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(isNull,
3756 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType),
3757 temp.getPointer(), "icr.argument");
3758
3759 // If we need to copy, then the load has to be conditional, which
3760 // means we need control flow.
3761 if (shouldCopy) {
3762 originBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3763 contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.cont");
3764 llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.copy");
3765 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, copyBB);
3766 CGF.EmitBlock(copyBB);
3767 condEval.begin(CGF);
3768 }
3769 }
3770
3771 llvm::Value *valueToUse = nullptr;
3772
3773 // Perform a copy if necessary.
3774 if (shouldCopy) {
3775 RValue srcRV = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(srcLV, SourceLocation());
3776 assert(srcRV.isScalar());
3777
3778 llvm::Value *src = srcRV.getScalarVal();
3779 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, destType->getElementType(),
3780 "icr.cast");
3781
3782 // Use an ordinary store, not a store-to-lvalue.
3783 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(src, temp);
3784
3785 // If optimization is enabled, and the value was held in a
3786 // __strong variable, we need to tell the optimizer that this
3787 // value has to stay alive until we're doing the store back.
3788 // This is because the temporary is effectively unretained,
3789 // and so otherwise we can violate the high-level semantics.
3790 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0 &&
3791 srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
3792 valueToUse = src;
3793 }
3794 }
3795
3796 // Finish the control flow if we needed it.
3797 if (shouldCopy && !provablyNonNull) {
3798 llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3799 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
3800
3801 // Make a phi for the value to intrinsically use.
3802 if (valueToUse) {
3803 llvm::PHINode *phiToUse = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(valueToUse->getType(), 2,
3804 "icr.to-use");
3805 phiToUse->addIncoming(valueToUse, copyBB);
3806 phiToUse->addIncoming(llvm::UndefValue::get(valueToUse->getType()),
3807 originBB);
3808 valueToUse = phiToUse;
3809 }
3810
3811 condEval.end(CGF);
3812 }
3813
3814 args.addWriteback(srcLV, temp, valueToUse);
3815 args.add(RValue::get(finalArgument), CRE->getType());
3816}

3818void CallArgList::allocateArgumentMemory(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
3819 assert(!StackBase);
3820
3821 // Save the stack.
3822 llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::stacksave);
3823 StackBase = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, {}, "inalloca.save");
3824}
3825
3826void CallArgList::freeArgumentMemory(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
3827 if (StackBase) {
3828 // Restore the stack after the call.
3829 llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::stackrestore);
3830 CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, StackBase);
3831 }

3834void CodeGenFunction::EmitNonNullArgCheck(RValue RV, QualType ArgType,
3835 SourceLocation ArgLoc,
3836 AbstractCallee AC,
3837 unsigned ParmNum) {
3838 if (!AC.getDecl() || !(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute) ||
3839 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg)))
3840 return;
3841
3842 // The param decl may be missing in a variadic function.
3843 auto PVD = ParmNum < AC.getNumParams() ? AC.getParamDecl(ParmNum) : nullptr;
3844 unsigned ArgNo = PVD ? PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex() : ParmNum;
3845
3846 // Prefer the nonnull attribute if it's present.
3847 const NonNullAttr *NNAttr = nullptr;
3848 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute))
3849 NNAttr = getNonNullAttr(AC.getDecl(), PVD, ArgType, ArgNo);
3850
3851 bool CanCheckNullability = false;
3852 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg) && !NNAttr && PVD) {
3853 auto Nullability = PVD->getType()->getNullability(getContext());
3854 CanCheckNullability = Nullability &&
3855 *Nullability == NullabilityKind::NonNull &&
3856 PVD->getTypeSourceInfo();
3857 }
3858
3859 if (!NNAttr && !CanCheckNullability)
3860 return;
3861
3862 SourceLocation AttrLoc;
3863 SanitizerMask CheckKind;
3864 SanitizerHandler Handler;
3865 if (NNAttr) {
3866 AttrLoc = NNAttr->getLocation();
3867 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute;
3868 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullArg;
3869 } else {
3870 AttrLoc = PVD->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
3871 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg;
3872 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityArg;
3873 }
3874
3875 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3876 llvm::Value *Cond = EmitNonNullRValueCheck(RV, ArgType);
3877 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
3878 EmitCheckSourceLocation(ArgLoc), EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc),
3879 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, ArgNo + 1),
3880 };
3881 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, None);
3882}

3884// Check if the call is going to use the inalloca convention. This needs to
3885// agree with CGFunctionInfo::usesInAlloca. The CGFunctionInfo is arranged
3886// later, so we can't check it directly.
3887static bool hasInAllocaArgs(CodeGenModule &CGM, CallingConv ExplicitCC,
3888 ArrayRef<QualType> ArgTypes) {
3889 // The Swift calling convention doesn't go through the target-specific
3890 // argument classification, so it never uses inalloca.
3891 // TODO: Consider limiting inalloca use to only calling conventions supported
3892 // by MSVC.
3893 if (ExplicitCC == CC_Swift)
3894 return false;
3895 if (!CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
3896 return false;
3897 return llvm::any_of(ArgTypes, [&](QualType Ty) {
3898 return isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), Ty);
3899 });
3900}

3903// Determine whether the given argument is an Objective-C method
3904// that may have type parameters in its signature.
3905static bool isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(const ObjCMethodDecl *method) {
3906 const DeclContext *dc = method->getDeclContext();
3907 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *classDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(dc)) {
3908 return classDecl->getTypeParamListAsWritten();
3909 }
3910
3911 if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *catDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(dc)) {
3912 return catDecl->getTypeParamList();
3913 }
3914
3915 return false;
3916}

3919/// EmitCallArgs - Emit call arguments for a function.
3920void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArgs(
3921 CallArgList &Args, PrototypeWrapper Prototype,
3922 llvm::iterator_range<CallExpr::const_arg_iterator> ArgRange,
3923 AbstractCallee AC, unsigned ParamsToSkip, EvaluationOrder Order) {
3924 SmallVector<QualType, 16> ArgTypes;
3925
3926 assert((ParamsToSkip == 0 || Prototype.P) &&
3927 "Can't skip parameters if type info is not provided");
3928
3929 // This variable only captures *explicitly* written conventions, not those
3930 // applied by default via command line flags or target defaults, such as
3931 // thiscall, aapcs, stdcall via -mrtd, etc. Computing that correctly would
3932 // require knowing if this is a C++ instance method or being able to see
3933 // unprototyped FunctionTypes.
3934 CallingConv ExplicitCC = CC_C;
3935
3936 // First, if a prototype was provided, use those argument types.
3937 bool IsVariadic = false;
3938 if (Prototype.P) {
3939 const auto *MD = Prototype.P.dyn_cast<const ObjCMethodDecl *>();
3940 if (MD) {
3941 IsVariadic = MD->isVariadic();
3942 ExplicitCC = getCallingConventionForDecl(
3943 MD, CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows());
3944 ArgTypes.assign(MD->param_type_begin() + ParamsToSkip,
3945 MD->param_type_end());
3946 } else {
3947 const auto *FPT = Prototype.P.get<const FunctionProtoType *>();
3948 IsVariadic = FPT->isVariadic();
3949 ExplicitCC = FPT->getExtInfo().getCC();
3950 ArgTypes.assign(FPT->param_type_begin() + ParamsToSkip,
3951 FPT->param_type_end());
3952 }
3953
3954#ifndef NDEBUG
3955 // Check that the prototyped types match the argument expression types.
3956 bool isGenericMethod = MD && isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(MD);
3957 CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin();
3958 for (QualType Ty : ArgTypes) {
3959 assert(Arg != ArgRange.end() && "Running over edge of argument list!");
3960 assert(
3961 (isGenericMethod || Ty->isVariablyModifiedType() ||
3962 Ty.getNonReferenceType()->isObjCRetainableType() ||
3963 getContext()
3964 .getCanonicalType(Ty.getNonReferenceType())
3965 .getTypePtr() ==
3966 getContext().getCanonicalType((*Arg)->getType()).getTypePtr()) &&
3967 "type mismatch in call argument!");
3968 ++Arg;
3969 }
3970
3971 // Either we've emitted all the call args, or we have a call to variadic
3972 // function.
3973 assert((Arg == ArgRange.end() || IsVariadic) &&
3974 "Extra arguments in non-variadic function!");
3975#endif
3976 }
3977
3978 // If we still have any arguments, emit them using the type of the argument.
3979 for (auto *A : llvm::make_range(std::next(ArgRange.begin(), ArgTypes.size()),
3980 ArgRange.end()))
3981 ArgTypes.push_back(IsVariadic ? getVarArgType(A) : A->getType());
3982 assert((int)ArgTypes.size() == (ArgRange.end() - ArgRange.begin()));
3983
3984 // We must evaluate arguments from right to left in the MS C++ ABI,
3985 // because arguments are destroyed left to right in the callee. As a special
3986 // case, there are certain language constructs that require left-to-right
3987 // evaluation, and in those cases we consider the evaluation order requirement
3988 // to trump the "destruction order is reverse construction order" guarantee.
3989 bool LeftToRight =
3990 CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()
3991 ? Order == EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight
3992 : Order != EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
3993
3994 auto MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize = [&](unsigned I, const Expr *Arg,
3995 RValue EmittedArg) {
3996 if (!AC.hasFunctionDecl() || I >= AC.getNumParams())
3997 return;
3998 auto *PS = AC.getParamDecl(I)->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
3999 if (PS == nullptr)
4000 return;
4001
4002 const auto &Context = getContext();
4003 auto SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
4004 auto T = Builder.getIntNTy(Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy));
4005 assert(EmittedArg.getScalarVal() && "We emitted nothing for the arg?");
4006 llvm::Value *V = evaluateOrEmitBuiltinObjectSize(Arg, PS->getType(), T,
4007 EmittedArg.getScalarVal(),
4008 PS->isDynamic());
4009 Args.add(RValue::get(V), SizeTy);
4010 // If we're emitting args in reverse, be sure to do so with
4011 // pass_object_size, as well.
4012 if (!LeftToRight)
4013 std::swap(Args.back(), *(&Args.back() - 1));
4014 };
4015
4016 // Insert a stack save if we're going to need any inalloca args.
4017 if (hasInAllocaArgs(CGM, ExplicitCC, ArgTypes)) {
4018 assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86 &&
4019 "inalloca only supported on x86");
4020 Args.allocateArgumentMemory(*this);
4021 }
4022
4023 // Evaluate each argument in the appropriate order.
4024 size_t CallArgsStart = Args.size();
4025 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ArgTypes.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4026 unsigned Idx = LeftToRight ? I : E - I - 1;
4027 CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin() + Idx;
4028 unsigned InitialArgSize = Args.size();
4029 // If *Arg is an ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr, check that either the types of
4030 // the argument and parameter match or the objc method is parameterized.
4031 assert((!isa<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(*Arg) ||
4032 getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType((*Arg)->getType(),
4033 ArgTypes[Idx]) ||
4034 (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl()) &&
4035 isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl())))) &&
4036 "Argument and parameter types don't match");
4037 EmitCallArg(Args, *Arg, ArgTypes[Idx]);
4038 // In particular, we depend on it being the last arg in Args, and the
4039 // objectsize bits depend on there only being one arg if !LeftToRight.
4040 assert(InitialArgSize + 1 == Args.size() &&
4041 "The code below depends on only adding one arg per EmitCallArg");
4042 (void)InitialArgSize;
4043 // Since pointer argument are never emitted as LValue, it is safe to emit
4044 // non-null argument check for r-value only.
4045 if (!Args.back().hasLValue()) {
4046 RValue RVArg = Args.back().getKnownRValue();
4047 EmitNonNullArgCheck(RVArg, ArgTypes[Idx], (*Arg)->getExprLoc(), AC,
4048 ParamsToSkip + Idx);
4049 // @llvm.objectsize should never have side-effects and shouldn't need
4050 // destruction/cleanups, so we can safely "emit" it after its arg,
4051 // regardless of right-to-leftness
4052 MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize(Idx, *Arg, RVArg);
4053 }
4054 }
4055
4056 if (!LeftToRight) {
4057 // Un-reverse the arguments we just evaluated so they match up with the LLVM
4058 // IR function.
4059 std::reverse(Args.begin() + CallArgsStart, Args.end());
4060 }
4061}

4100RValue CallArg::getRValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
4101 if (!HasLV)
4102 return RV;
4103 LValue Copy = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty), Ty);
4104 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Copy, LV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,

4110void CallArg::copyInto(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Addr) const {
4111 LValue Dst = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
4112 if (!HasLV && RV.isScalar())
4113 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(RV.getScalarVal(), Dst, /*isInit=*/true);
4114 else if (!HasLV && RV.isComplex())
4115 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(RV.getComplexVal(), Dst, /*init=*/true);
4116 else {
4117 auto Addr = HasLV ? LV.getAddress(CGF) : RV.getAggregateAddress();
4118 LValue SrcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
4119 // We assume that call args are never copied into subobjects.
4120 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dst, SrcLV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
4121 HasLV ? LV.isVolatileQualified()
4122 : RV.isVolatileQualified());
4123 }
4124 IsUsed = true;
4125}
4126
4127void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArg(CallArgList &args, const Expr *E,
4128 QualType type) {
4129 DisableDebugLocationUpdates Dis(*this, E);
4130 if (const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE
4131 = dyn_cast<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(E)) {
4132 assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
4133 return emitWritebackArg(*this, args, CRE);
4134 }
4135
4136 assert(type->isReferenceType() == E->isGLValue() &&
4137 "reference binding to unmaterialized r-value!");
4138
4139 if (E->isGLValue()) {
4140 assert(E->getObjectKind() == OK_Ordinary);
4141 return args.add(EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(E), type);
4142 }
4143
4144 bool HasAggregateEvalKind = hasAggregateEvaluationKind(type);
4145
4146 // In the Microsoft C++ ABI, aggregate arguments are destructed by the callee.
4147 // However, we still have to push an EH-only cleanup in case we unwind before
4148 // we make it to the call.
4149 if (HasAggregateEvalKind &&
4150 type->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee()) {
4151 // If we're using inalloca, use the argument memory. Otherwise, use a
4152 // temporary.
4153 AggValueSlot Slot;
4154 if (args.isUsingInAlloca())
4155 Slot = createPlaceholderSlot(*this, type);
4156 else
4157 Slot = CreateAggTemp(type, "agg.tmp");
4158
4159 bool DestroyedInCallee = true, NeedsEHCleanup = true;
4160 if (const auto *RD = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4161 DestroyedInCallee = RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor();
4162 else
4163 NeedsEHCleanup = needsEHCleanup(type.isDestructedType());
4164
4165 if (DestroyedInCallee)
4166 Slot.setExternallyDestructed();
4167
4168 EmitAggExpr(E, Slot);
4169 RValue RV = Slot.asRValue();
4170 args.add(RV, type);
4171
4172 if (DestroyedInCallee && NeedsEHCleanup) {
4173 // Create a no-op GEP between the placeholder and the cleanup so we can
4174 // RAUW it successfully. It also serves as a marker of the first
4175 // instruction where the cleanup is active.
4176 pushFullExprCleanup<DestroyUnpassedArg>(EHCleanup, Slot.getAddress(),
4177 type);
4178 // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
4179 llvm::Instruction *IsActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4180 args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(EHStack.getInnermostEHScope(), IsActive);
4181 }
4182 return;
4183 }
4184
4185 if (HasAggregateEvalKind && isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(E) &&
4186 cast<CastExpr>(E)->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue) {
4187 LValue L = EmitLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
4188 assert(L.isSimple());
4189 args.addUncopiedAggregate(L, type);
4190 return;
4191 }
4192
4193 args.add(EmitAnyExprToTemp(E), type);
4194}
4195
4196QualType CodeGenFunction::getVarArgType(const Expr *Arg) {
4197 // System headers on Windows define NULL to 0 instead of 0LL on Win64. MSVC
4198 // implicitly widens null pointer constants that are arguments to varargs
4199 // functions to pointer-sized ints.
4200 if (!getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows())
4201 return Arg->getType();
4202
4203 if (Arg->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
4204 getContext().getTypeSize(Arg->getType()) <
4205 getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) &&
4206 Arg->isNullPointerConstant(getContext(),
4207 Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
4208 return getContext().getIntPtrType();
4209 }
4210
4211 return Arg->getType();
4212}

4248// Calls which may throw must have operand bundles indicating which funclet
4249// they are nested within.
4250SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1>
4251CodeGenFunction::getBundlesForFunclet(llvm::Value *Callee) {
4252 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList;
4253 // There is no need for a funclet operand bundle if we aren't inside a
4254 // funclet.
4255 if (!CurrentFuncletPad)
4256 return BundleList;
4257
4258 // Skip intrinsics which cannot throw.
4259 auto *CalleeFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Callee->stripPointerCasts());
4260 if (CalleeFn && CalleeFn->isIntrinsic() && CalleeFn->doesNotThrow())
4261 return BundleList;
4262
4263 BundleList.emplace_back("funclet", CurrentFuncletPad);
4264 return BundleList;
4265}

4269 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> args,
4270 const llvm::Twine &name) {
4271 llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(
4272 callee, args, getBundlesForFunclet(callee.getCallee()), name);
4273 call->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4274 return call;
4275}

4277/// Emits a call or invoke to the given noreturn runtime function.
4278void CodeGenFunction::EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(
4279 llvm::FunctionCallee callee, ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> args) {
4280 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
4281 getBundlesForFunclet(callee.getCallee());
4282
4283 if (getInvokeDest()) {
4284 llvm::InvokeInst *invoke =
4285 Builder.CreateInvoke(callee,
4286 getUnreachableBlock(),
4287 getInvokeDest(),
4288 args,
4289 BundleList);
4290 invoke->setDoesNotReturn();
4291 invoke->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4292 } else {
4293 llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(callee, args, BundleList);
4294 call->setDoesNotReturn();
4295 call->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4296 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4297 }
4298}

4316
4317/// Emits a call or invoke instruction to the given function, depending
4318/// on the current state of the EH stack.
4319llvm::CallBase *CodeGenFunction::EmitCallOrInvoke(llvm::FunctionCallee Callee,
4320 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args,
4321 const Twine &Name) {
4322 llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = getInvokeDest();
4323 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
4324 getBundlesForFunclet(Callee.getCallee());
4325
4326 llvm::CallBase *Inst;
4327 if (!InvokeDest)
4328 Inst = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args, BundleList, Name);
4329 else {
4330 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
4331 Inst = Builder.CreateInvoke(Callee, ContBB, InvokeDest, Args, BundleList,
4332 Name);
4333 EmitBlock(ContBB);
4334 }
4335
4336 // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
4337 // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
4338 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
4339 AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(Inst);
4340
4341 return Inst;
4342}

4345 llvm::Value *New) {
4346 DeferredReplacements.push_back(std::make_pair(Old, New));
4347}

4351/// Specify given \p NewAlign as the alignment of return value attribute. If
4352/// such attribute already exists, re-set it to the maximal one of two options.
4353LLVM_NODISCARD llvm::AttributeList
4354maybeRaiseRetAlignmentAttribute(llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx,
4355 const llvm::AttributeList &Attrs,
4356 llvm::Align NewAlign) {
4357 llvm::Align CurAlign = Attrs.getRetAlignment().valueOrOne();
4358 if (CurAlign >= NewAlign)
4359 return Attrs;
4360 llvm::Attribute AlignAttr = llvm::Attribute::getWithAlignment(Ctx, NewAlign);
4361 return Attrs
4362 .removeAttribute(Ctx, llvm::AttributeList::ReturnIndex,
4363 llvm::Attribute::AttrKind::Alignment)
4364 .addAttribute(Ctx, llvm::AttributeList::ReturnIndex, AlignAttr);
4365}
4366
4367template <typename AlignedAttrTy> class AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter {
4368protected:
4369 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
4370
4371 /// We do nothing if this is, or becomes, nullptr.
4372 const AlignedAttrTy *AA = nullptr;
4373
4374 llvm::Value *Alignment = nullptr; // May or may not be a constant.
4375 llvm::ConstantInt *OffsetCI = nullptr; // Constant, hopefully zero.
4376
4377 AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl)
4378 : CGF(CGF_) {
4379 if (!FuncDecl)
4380 return;
4381 AA = FuncDecl->getAttr<AlignedAttrTy>();
4382 }
4383
4384public:
4385 /// If we can, materialize the alignment as an attribute on return value.
4386 LLVM_NODISCARD llvm::AttributeList
4387 TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(const llvm::AttributeList &Attrs) {
4388 if (!AA || OffsetCI || CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment))
4389 return Attrs;
4390 const auto *AlignmentCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Alignment);
4391 if (!AlignmentCI)
4392 return Attrs;
4393 // We may legitimately have non-power-of-2 alignment here.
4394 // If so, this is UB land, emit it via `@llvm.assume` instead.
4395 if (!AlignmentCI->getValue().isPowerOf2())
4396 return Attrs;
4397 llvm::AttributeList NewAttrs = maybeRaiseRetAlignmentAttribute(
4398 CGF.getLLVMContext(), Attrs,
4399 llvm::Align(
4400 AlignmentCI->getLimitedValue(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment)));
4401 AA = nullptr; // We're done. Disallow doing anything else.
4402 return NewAttrs;
4403 }
4404
4405 /// Emit alignment assumption.
4406 /// This is a general fallback that we take if either there is an offset,
4407 /// or the alignment is variable or we are sanitizing for alignment.
4408 void EmitAsAnAssumption(SourceLocation Loc, QualType RetTy, RValue &Ret) {
4409 if (!AA)
4410 return;
4411 CGF.emitAlignmentAssumption(Ret.getScalarVal(), RetTy, Loc,
4412 AA->getLocation(), Alignment, OffsetCI);
4413 AA = nullptr; // We're done. Disallow doing anything else.
4414 }
4415};
4416
4417/// Helper data structure to emit `AssumeAlignedAttr`.
4418class AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter final
4419 : public AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter<AssumeAlignedAttr> {
4420public:
4421 AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl)
4422 : AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CGF_, FuncDecl) {
4423 if (!AA)
4424 return;
4425 // It is guaranteed that the alignment/offset are constants.
4426 Alignment = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(AA->getAlignment()));
4427 if (Expr *Offset = AA->getOffset()) {
4428 OffsetCI = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Offset));
4429 if (OffsetCI->isNullValue()) // Canonicalize zero offset to no offset.
4430 OffsetCI = nullptr;
4431 }
4432 }
4433};
4434
4435/// Helper data structure to emit `AllocAlignAttr`.
4436class AllocAlignAttrEmitter final
4437 : public AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter<AllocAlignAttr> {
4438public:
4439 AllocAlignAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl,
4440 const CallArgList &CallArgs)
4441 : AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CGF_, FuncDecl) {
4442 if (!AA)
4443 return;
4444 // Alignment may or may not be a constant, and that is okay.
4445 Alignment = CallArgs[AA->getParamIndex().getLLVMIndex()]
4446 .getRValue(CGF)
4447 .getScalarVal();
4448 }
4449};
4450
4451} // namespace
4452
4453RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(const CGFunctionInfo &CallInfo,
4454 const CGCallee &Callee,
4455 ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
4456 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
4457 llvm::CallBase **callOrInvoke,
4458 SourceLocation Loc) {
4459 // FIXME: We no longer need the types from CallArgs; lift up and simplify.
4460
4461 assert(Callee.isOrdinary() || Callee.isVirtual());
4462
4463 // Handle struct-return functions by passing a pointer to the
4464 // location that we would like to return into.
4465 QualType RetTy = CallInfo.getReturnType();
4466 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = CallInfo.getReturnInfo();
4467
4468 llvm::FunctionType *IRFuncTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(CallInfo);
4469
4470 const Decl *TargetDecl = Callee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
4471 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
4472 // We can only guarantee that a function is called from the correct
4473 // context/function based on the appropriate target attributes,
4474 // so only check in the case where we have both always_inline and target
4475 // since otherwise we could be making a conditional call after a check for
4476 // the proper cpu features (and it won't cause code generation issues due to
4477 // function based code generation).
4478 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
4479 TargetDecl->hasAttr<TargetAttr>())
4480 checkTargetFeatures(Loc, FD);
4481
4482 // Some architectures (such as x86-64) have the ABI changed based on
4483 // attribute-target/features. Give them a chance to diagnose.
4484 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().checkFunctionCallABI(
4485 CGM, Loc, dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl), FD, CallArgs);
4486 }
4487
4488#ifndef NDEBUG
4489 if (!(CallInfo.isVariadic() && CallInfo.getArgStruct())) {
4490 // For an inalloca varargs function, we don't expect CallInfo to match the
4491 // function pointer's type, because the inalloca struct a will have extra
4492 // fields in it for the varargs parameters. Code later in this function
4493 // bitcasts the function pointer to the type derived from CallInfo.
4494 //
4495 // In other cases, we assert that the types match up (until pointers stop
4496 // having pointee types).
4497 llvm::Type *TypeFromVal;
4498 if (Callee.isVirtual())
4499 TypeFromVal = Callee.getVirtualFunctionType();
4500 else
4501 TypeFromVal =
4502 Callee.getFunctionPointer()->getType()->getPointerElementType();
4503 assert(IRFuncTy == TypeFromVal);
4504 }
4505#endif
4506
4507 // 1. Set up the arguments.
4508
4509 // If we're using inalloca, insert the allocation after the stack save.
4510 // FIXME: Do this earlier rather than hacking it in here!
4511 Address ArgMemory = Address::invalid();
4512 if (llvm::StructType *ArgStruct = CallInfo.getArgStruct()) {
4513 const llvm::DataLayout &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
4514 llvm::Instruction *IP = CallArgs.getStackBase();
4515 llvm::AllocaInst *AI;
4516 if (IP) {
4517 IP = IP->getNextNode();
4518 AI = new llvm::AllocaInst(ArgStruct, DL.getAllocaAddrSpace(),
4519 "argmem", IP);
4520 } else {
4521 AI = CreateTempAlloca(ArgStruct, "argmem");
4522 }
4523 auto Align = CallInfo.getArgStructAlignment();
4524 AI->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
4525 AI->setUsedWithInAlloca(true);
4526 assert(AI->isUsedWithInAlloca() && !AI->isStaticAlloca());
4527 ArgMemory = Address(AI, Align);
4528 }
4529
4530 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), CallInfo);
4531 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> IRCallArgs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
4532
4533 // If the call returns a temporary with struct return, create a temporary
4534 // alloca to hold the result, unless one is given to us.
4535 Address SRetPtr = Address::invalid();
4536 Address SRetAlloca = Address::invalid();
4537 llvm::Value *UnusedReturnSizePtr = nullptr;
4538 if (RetAI.isIndirect() || RetAI.isInAlloca() || RetAI.isCoerceAndExpand()) {
4539 if (!ReturnValue.isNull()) {
4540 SRetPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
4541 } else {
4542 SRetPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "tmp", &SRetAlloca);
4543 if (HaveInsertPoint() && ReturnValue.isUnused()) {
4544 uint64_t size =
4545 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ConvertTypeForMem(RetTy));
4546 UnusedReturnSizePtr = EmitLifetimeStart(size, SRetAlloca.getPointer());
4547 }
4548 }
4549 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
4550 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] = SRetPtr.getPointer();
4551 } else if (RetAI.isInAlloca()) {
4552 Address Addr =
4553 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4554 Builder.CreateStore(SRetPtr.getPointer(), Addr);
4555 }
4556 }
4557
4558 Address swiftErrorTemp = Address::invalid();
4559 Address swiftErrorArg = Address::invalid();
4560
4561 // When passing arguments using temporary allocas, we need to add the
4562 // appropriate lifetime markers. This vector keeps track of all the lifetime
4563 // markers that need to be ended right after the call.
4564 SmallVector<CallLifetimeEnd, 2> CallLifetimeEndAfterCall;
4565
4566 // Translate all of the arguments as necessary to match the IR lowering.
4567 assert(CallInfo.arg_size() == CallArgs.size() &&
4568 "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
4569 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
4570 CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = CallInfo.arg_begin();
4571 for (CallArgList::const_iterator I = CallArgs.begin(), E = CallArgs.end();
4572 I != E; ++I, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
4573 const ABIArgInfo &ArgInfo = info_it->info;
4574
4575 // Insert a padding argument to ensure proper alignment.
4576 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo))
4577 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
4578 llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgInfo.getPaddingType());
4579
4580 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
4581 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
4582
4583 switch (ArgInfo.getKind()) {
4584 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
4585 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
4586 assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86);
4587 if (I->isAggregate()) {
4588 Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
4589 ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4590 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4591 llvm::Instruction *Placeholder =
4592 cast<llvm::Instruction>(Addr.getPointer());
4593
4594 if (!ArgInfo.getInAllocaIndirect()) {
4595 // Replace the placeholder with the appropriate argument slot GEP.
4596 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint IP = Builder.saveIP();
4597 Builder.SetInsertPoint(Placeholder);
4598 Addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory,
4599 ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4600 Builder.restoreIP(IP);
4601 } else {
4602 // For indirect things such as overaligned structs, replace the
4603 // placeholder with a regular aggregate temporary alloca. Store the
4604 // address of this alloca into the struct.
4605 Addr = CreateMemTemp(info_it->type, "inalloca.indirect.tmp");
4606 Address ArgSlot = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
4607 ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4608 Builder.CreateStore(Addr.getPointer(), ArgSlot);
4609 }
4610 deferPlaceholderReplacement(Placeholder, Addr.getPointer());
4611 } else if (ArgInfo.getInAllocaIndirect()) {
4612 // Make a temporary alloca and store the address of it into the argument
4613 // struct.
4614 Address Addr = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4615 I->Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(I->Ty),
4616 "indirect-arg-temp");
4617 I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4618 Address ArgSlot =
4619 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4620 Builder.CreateStore(Addr.getPointer(), ArgSlot);
4621 } else {
4622 // Store the RValue into the argument struct.
4623 Address Addr =
4624 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4625 unsigned AS = Addr.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
4626 llvm::Type *MemType = ConvertTypeForMem(I->Ty)->getPointerTo(AS);
4627 // There are some cases where a trivial bitcast is not avoidable. The
4628 // definition of a type later in a translation unit may change it's type
4629 // from {}* to (%struct.foo*)*.
4630 if (Addr.getType() != MemType)
4631 Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, MemType);
4632 I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4633 }
4634 break;
4635 }
4636
4637 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
4638 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
4639 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4640 if (!I->isAggregate()) {
4641 // Make a temporary alloca to pass the argument.
4642 Address Addr = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4643 I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "indirect-arg-temp");
4644 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = Addr.getPointer();
4645
4646 I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4647 } else {
4648 // We want to avoid creating an unnecessary temporary+copy here;
4649 // however, we need one in three cases:
4650 // 1. If the argument is not byval, and we are required to copy the
4651 // source. (This case doesn't occur on any common architecture.)
4652 // 2. If the argument is byval, RV is not sufficiently aligned, and
4653 // we cannot force it to be sufficiently aligned.
4654 // 3. If the argument is byval, but RV is not located in default
4655 // or alloca address space.
4656 Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
4657 ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4658 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4659 llvm::Value *V = Addr.getPointer();
4660 CharUnits Align = ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign();
4661 const llvm::DataLayout *TD = &CGM.getDataLayout();
4662
4663 assert((FirstIRArg >= IRFuncTy->getNumParams() ||
4664 IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
4665 TD->getAllocaAddrSpace()) &&
4666 "indirect argument must be in alloca address space");
4667
4668 bool NeedCopy = false;
4669
4670 if (Addr.getAlignment() < Align &&
4671 llvm::getOrEnforceKnownAlignment(V, Align.getAsAlign(), *TD) <
4672 Align.getAsAlign()) {
4673 NeedCopy = true;
4674 } else if (I->hasLValue()) {
4675 auto LV = I->getKnownLValue();
4676 auto AS = LV.getAddressSpace();
4677
4678 if (!ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() ||
4679 (LV.getAlignment() < getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(I->Ty))) {
4680 NeedCopy = true;
4681 }
4682 if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4683 if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4684 (AS != LangAS::Default &&
4685 AS != CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace()))) {
4686 NeedCopy = true;
4687 }
4688 }
4689 // For OpenCL even if RV is located in default or alloca address space
4690 // we don't want to perform address space cast for it.
4691 else if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4692 Addr.getType()->getAddressSpace() != IRFuncTy->
4693 getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace())) {
4694 NeedCopy = true;
4695 }
4696 }
4697
4698 if (NeedCopy) {
4699 // Create an aligned temporary, and copy to it.
4700 Address AI = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4701 I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "byval-temp");
4702 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = AI.getPointer();
4703
4704 // Emit lifetime markers for the temporary alloca.
4705 uint64_t ByvalTempElementSize =
4706 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getElementType());
4707 llvm::Value *LifetimeSize =
4708 EmitLifetimeStart(ByvalTempElementSize, AI.getPointer());
4709
4710 // Add cleanup code to emit the end lifetime marker after the call.
4711 if (LifetimeSize) // In case we disabled lifetime markers.
4712 CallLifetimeEndAfterCall.emplace_back(AI, LifetimeSize);
4713
4714 // Generate the copy.
4715 I->copyInto(*this, AI);
4716 } else {
4717 // Skip the extra memcpy call.
4718 auto *T = V->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(
4719 CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace());
4720 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
4721 *this, V, LangAS::Default, CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), T,
4722 true);
4723 }
4724 }
4725 break;
4726 }
4727
4728 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
4729 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
4730 break;
4731
4732 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
4733 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
4734 if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType()) &&
4735 ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(info_it->type) &&
4736 ArgInfo.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
4737 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4738 llvm::Value *V;
4739 if (!I->isAggregate())
4740 V = I->getKnownRValue().getScalarVal();
4741 else
4742 V = Builder.CreateLoad(
4743 I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4744 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress());
4745
4746 // Implement swifterror by copying into a new swifterror argument.
4747 // We'll write back in the normal path out of the call.
4748 if (CallInfo.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
4749 == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
4750 assert(!swiftErrorTemp.isValid() && "multiple swifterror args");
4751
4752 QualType pointeeTy = I->Ty->getPointeeType();
4753 swiftErrorArg =
4754 Address(V, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
4755
4756 swiftErrorTemp =
4757 CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
4758 V = swiftErrorTemp.getPointer();
4759 cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(V)->setSwiftError(true);
4760
4761 llvm::Value *errorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorArg);
4762 Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, swiftErrorTemp);
4763 }
4764
4765 // We might have to widen integers, but we should never truncate.
4766 if (ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() != V->getType() &&
4767 V->getType()->isIntegerTy())
4768 V = Builder.CreateZExt(V, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
4769
4770 // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
4771 // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
4772 if (FirstIRArg < IRFuncTy->getNumParams() &&
4773 V->getType() != IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg))
4774 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg));
4775
4776 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = V;
4777 break;
4778 }
4779
4780 // FIXME: Avoid the conversion through memory if possible.
4781 Address Src = Address::invalid();
4782 if (!I->isAggregate()) {
4783 Src = CreateMemTemp(I->Ty, "coerce");
4784 I->copyInto(*this, Src);
4785 } else {
4786 Src = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4787 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4788 }
4789
4790 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
4791 Src = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Src, ArgInfo);
4792
4793 // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
4794 // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
4795 llvm::StructType *STy =
4796 dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
4797 if (STy && ArgInfo.isDirect() && ArgInfo.getCanBeFlattened()) {
4798 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src.getElementType();
4799 uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
4800 uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
4801
4802 // If the source type is smaller than the destination type of the
4803 // coerce-to logic, copy the source value into a temp alloca the size
4804 // of the destination type to allow loading all of it. The bits past
4805 // the source value are left undef.
4806 if (SrcSize < DstSize) {
4807 Address TempAlloca
4808 = CreateTempAlloca(STy, Src.getAlignment(),
4809 Src.getName() + ".coerce");
4810 Builder.CreateMemCpy(TempAlloca, Src, SrcSize);
4811 Src = TempAlloca;
4812 } else {
4813 Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src,
4814 STy->getPointerTo(Src.getAddressSpace()));
4815 }
4816
4817 assert(NumIRArgs == STy->getNumElements());
4818 for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
4819 Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Src, i);
4820 llvm::Value *LI = Builder.CreateLoad(EltPtr);
4821 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg + i] = LI;
4822 }
4823 } else {
4824 // In the simple case, just pass the coerced loaded value.
4825 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4826 llvm::Value *Load =
4827 CreateCoercedLoad(Src, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType(), *this);
4828
4829 if (CallInfo.isCmseNSCall()) {
4830 // For certain parameter types, clear padding bits, as they may reveal
4831 // sensitive information.
4832 // Small struct/union types are passed as integer arrays.
4833 auto *ATy = dyn_cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Load->getType());
4834 if (ATy != nullptr && isa<RecordType>(I->Ty.getCanonicalType()))
4835 Load = EmitCMSEClearRecord(Load, ATy, I->Ty);
4836 }
4837 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = Load;
4838 }
4839
4840 break;
4841 }
4842
4843 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
4844 auto coercionType = ArgInfo.getCoerceAndExpandType();
4845 auto layout = CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(coercionType);
4846
4847 llvm::Value *tempSize = nullptr;
4848 Address addr = Address::invalid();
4849 Address AllocaAddr = Address::invalid();
4850 if (I->isAggregate()) {
4851 addr = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4852 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4853
4854 } else {
4855 RValue RV = I->getKnownRValue();
4856 assert(RV.isScalar()); // complex should always just be direct
4857
4858 llvm::Type *scalarType = RV.getScalarVal()->getType();
4859 auto scalarSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(scalarType);
4860 auto scalarAlign = CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(scalarType);
4861
4862 // Materialize to a temporary.
4863 addr = CreateTempAlloca(
4864 RV.getScalarVal()->getType(),
4865 CharUnits::fromQuantity(std::max(
4866 (unsigned)layout->getAlignment().value(), scalarAlign)),
4867 "tmp",
4868 /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, &AllocaAddr);
4869 tempSize = EmitLifetimeStart(scalarSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
4870
4871 Builder.CreateStore(RV.getScalarVal(), addr);
4872 }
4873
4874 addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
4875
4876 unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
4877 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
4878 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
4879 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
4880 Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
4881 llvm::Value *elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
4882 IRCallArgs[IRArgPos++] = elt;
4883 }
4884 assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
4885
4886 if (tempSize) {
4887 EmitLifetimeEnd(tempSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
4888 }
4889
4890 break;
4891 }
4892
4893 case ABIArgInfo::Expand: {
4894 unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
4895 ExpandTypeToArgs(I->Ty, *I, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs, IRArgPos);
4896 assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
4897 break;
4898 }
4899 }
4900 }
4901
4902 const CGCallee &ConcreteCallee = Callee.prepareConcreteCallee(*this);
4903 llvm::Value *CalleePtr = ConcreteCallee.getFunctionPointer();
4904
4905 // If we're using inalloca, set up that argument.
4906 if (ArgMemory.isValid()) {
4907 llvm::Value *Arg = ArgMemory.getPointer();
4908 if (CallInfo.isVariadic()) {
4909 // When passing non-POD arguments by value to variadic functions, we will
4910 // end up with a variadic prototype and an inalloca call site. In such
4911 // cases, we can't do any parameter mismatch checks. Give up and bitcast
4912 // the callee.
4913 unsigned CalleeAS = CalleePtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
4914 CalleePtr =
4915 Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, IRFuncTy->getPointerTo(CalleeAS));
4916 } else {
4917 llvm::Type *LastParamTy =
4918 IRFuncTy->getParamType(IRFuncTy->getNumParams() - 1);
4919 if (Arg->getType() != LastParamTy) {
4920#ifndef NDEBUG
4921 // Assert that these structs have equivalent element types.
4922 llvm::StructType *FullTy = CallInfo.getArgStruct();
4923 llvm::StructType *DeclaredTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(
4924 cast<llvm::PointerType>(LastParamTy)->getElementType());
4925 assert(DeclaredTy->getNumElements() == FullTy->getNumElements());
4926 for (llvm::StructType::element_iterator DI = DeclaredTy->element_begin(),
4927 DE = DeclaredTy->element_end(),
4928 FI = FullTy->element_begin();
4929 DI != DE; ++DI, ++FI)
4930 assert(*DI == *FI);
4931#endif
4932 Arg = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg, LastParamTy);
4933 }
4934 }
4935 assert(IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg());
4936 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] = Arg;
4937 }
4938
4939 // 2. Prepare the function pointer.
4940
4941 // If the callee is a bitcast of a non-variadic function to have a
4942 // variadic function pointer type, check to see if we can remove the
4943 // bitcast. This comes up with unprototyped functions.
4944 //
4945 // This makes the IR nicer, but more importantly it ensures that we
4946 // can inline the function at -O0 if it is marked always_inline.
4947 auto simplifyVariadicCallee = [](llvm::FunctionType *CalleeFT,
4948 llvm::Value *Ptr) -> llvm::Function * {
4949 if (!CalleeFT->isVarArg())
4950 return nullptr;
4951
4952 // Get underlying value if it's a bitcast
4953 if (llvm::ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Ptr)) {
4954 if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
4955 Ptr = CE->getOperand(0);
4956 }
4957
4958 llvm::Function *OrigFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Ptr);
4959 if (!OrigFn)
4960 return nullptr;
4961
4962 llvm::FunctionType *OrigFT = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
4963
4964 // If the original type is variadic, or if any of the component types
4965 // disagree, we cannot remove the cast.
4966 if (OrigFT->isVarArg() ||
4967 OrigFT->getNumParams() != CalleeFT->getNumParams() ||
4968 OrigFT->getReturnType() != CalleeFT->getReturnType())
4969 return nullptr;
4970
4971 for (unsigned i = 0, e = OrigFT->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i)
4972 if (OrigFT->getParamType(i) != CalleeFT->getParamType(i))
4973 return nullptr;
4974
4975 return OrigFn;
4976 };
4977
4978 if (llvm::Function *OrigFn = simplifyVariadicCallee(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr)) {
4979 CalleePtr = OrigFn;
4980 IRFuncTy = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
4981 }
4982
4983 // 3. Perform the actual call.
4984
4985 // Deactivate any cleanups that we're supposed to do immediately before
4986 // the call.
4987 if (!CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate().empty())
4988 deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(*this, CallArgs);
4989
4990 // Assert that the arguments we computed match up. The IR verifier
4991 // will catch this, but this is a common enough source of problems
4992 // during IRGen changes that it's way better for debugging to catch
4993 // it ourselves here.
4994#ifndef NDEBUG
4995 assert(IRCallArgs.size() == IRFuncTy->getNumParams() || IRFuncTy->isVarArg());
4996 for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
4997 // Inalloca argument can have different type.
4998 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg() &&
4999 i == IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo())
5000 continue;
5001 if (i < IRFuncTy->getNumParams())
5002 assert(IRCallArgs[i]->getType() == IRFuncTy->getParamType(i));
5003 }
5004#endif
5005
5006 // Update the largest vector width if any arguments have vector types.
5007 for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
5008 if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(IRCallArgs[i]->getType()))
5009 LargestVectorWidth =
5010 std::max((uint64_t)LargestVectorWidth,
5011 VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize());
5012 }
5013
5014 // Compute the calling convention and attributes.
5015 unsigned CallingConv;
5016 llvm::AttributeList Attrs;
5017 CGM.ConstructAttributeList(CalleePtr->getName(), CallInfo,
5018 Callee.getAbstractInfo(), Attrs, CallingConv,
5019 /*AttrOnCallSite=*/true);
5020
5021 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl))
5022 if (FD->hasAttr<StrictFPAttr>())
5023 // All calls within a strictfp function are marked strictfp
5024 Attrs =
5025 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5026 llvm::Attribute::StrictFP);
5027
5028 // Add call-site nomerge attribute if exists.
5029 if (InNoMergeAttributedStmt)
5030 Attrs =
5031 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5032 llvm::Attribute::NoMerge);
5033
5034 // Apply some call-site-specific attributes.
5035 // TODO: work this into building the attribute set.
5036
5037 // Apply always_inline to all calls within flatten functions.
5038 // FIXME: should this really take priority over __try, below?
5039 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<FlattenAttr>() &&
5040 !(TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>())) {
5041 Attrs =
5042 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5043 llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
5044 }
5045
5046 // Disable inlining inside SEH __try blocks.
5047 if (isSEHTryScope()) {
5048 Attrs =
5049 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5050 llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
5051 }
5052
5053 // Decide whether to use a call or an invoke.
5054 bool CannotThrow;
5055 if (currentFunctionUsesSEHTry()) {
5056 // SEH cares about asynchronous exceptions, so everything can "throw."
5057 CannotThrow = false;
5058 } else if (isCleanupPadScope() &&
5059 EHPersonality::get(*this).isMSVCXXPersonality()) {
5060 // The MSVC++ personality will implicitly terminate the program if an
5061 // exception is thrown during a cleanup outside of a try/catch.
5062 // We don't need to model anything in IR to get this behavior.
5063 CannotThrow = true;
5064 } else {
5065 // Otherwise, nounwind call sites will never throw.
5066 CannotThrow = Attrs.hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
5067
5068 if (auto *FPtr = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(CalleePtr))
5069 if (FPtr->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind))
5070 CannotThrow = true;
5071 }
5072
5073 // If we made a temporary, be sure to clean up after ourselves. Note that we
5074 // can't depend on being inside of an ExprWithCleanups, so we need to manually
5075 // pop this cleanup later on. Being eager about this is OK, since this
5076 // temporary is 'invisible' outside of the callee.
5077 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5078 pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, SRetAlloca,
5079 UnusedReturnSizePtr);
5080
5081 llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = CannotThrow ? nullptr : getInvokeDest();
5082
5083 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
5084 getBundlesForFunclet(CalleePtr);
5085
5086 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl))
5087 if (FD->hasAttr<StrictFPAttr>())
5088 // All calls within a strictfp function are marked strictfp
5089 Attrs =
5090 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5091 llvm::Attribute::StrictFP);
5092
5093 AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(*this, TargetDecl);
5094 Attrs = AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter.TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(Attrs);
5095
5096 AllocAlignAttrEmitter AllocAlignAttrEmitter(*this, TargetDecl, CallArgs);
5097 Attrs = AllocAlignAttrEmitter.TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(Attrs);
5098
5099 // Emit the actual call/invoke instruction.
5100 llvm::CallBase *CI;
5101 if (!InvokeDest) {
5102 CI = Builder.CreateCall(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, IRCallArgs, BundleList);
5103 } else {
5104 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
5105 CI = Builder.CreateInvoke(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, Cont, InvokeDest, IRCallArgs,
5106 BundleList);
5107 EmitBlock(Cont);
5108 }
5109 if (callOrInvoke)
5110 *callOrInvoke = CI;
5111
5112 // If this is within a function that has the guard(nocf) attribute and is an
5113 // indirect call, add the "guard_nocf" attribute to this call to indicate that
5114 // Control Flow Guard checks should not be added, even if the call is inlined.
5115 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl)) {
5116 if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<CFGuardAttr>()) {
5117 if (A->getGuard() == CFGuardAttr::GuardArg::nocf && !CI->getCalledFunction())
5118 Attrs = Attrs.addAttribute(
5119 getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, "guard_nocf");
5120 }
5121 }
5122
5123 // Apply the attributes and calling convention.
5124 CI->setAttributes(Attrs);
5125 CI->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(CallingConv));
5126
5127 // Apply various metadata.
5128
5129 if (!CI->getType()->isVoidTy())
5130 CI->setName("call");
5131
5132 // Update largest vector width from the return type.
5133 if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(CI->getType()))
5134 LargestVectorWidth =
5135 std::max((uint64_t)LargestVectorWidth,
5136 VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize());
5137
5138 // Insert instrumentation or attach profile metadata at indirect call sites.
5139 // For more details, see the comment before the definition of
5140 // IPVK_IndirectCallTarget in InstrProfData.inc.
5141 if (!CI->getCalledFunction())
5142 PGO.valueProfile(Builder, llvm::IPVK_IndirectCallTarget,
5143 CI, CalleePtr);
5144
5145 // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
5146 // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
5147 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
5148 AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(CI);
5149
5150 // Suppress tail calls if requested.
5151 if (llvm::CallInst *Call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(CI)) {
5152 if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NotTailCalledAttr>())
5153 Call->setTailCallKind(llvm::CallInst::TCK_NoTail);
5154 }
5155
5156 // Add metadata for calls to MSAllocator functions
5157 if (getDebugInfo() && TargetDecl &&
5158 TargetDecl->hasAttr<MSAllocatorAttr>())
5159 getDebugInfo()->addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(CI, RetTy->getPointeeType(), Loc);
5160
5161 // 4. Finish the call.
5162
5163 // If the call doesn't return, finish the basic block and clear the
5164 // insertion point; this allows the rest of IRGen to discard
5165 // unreachable code.
5166 if (CI->doesNotReturn()) {
5167 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5168 PopCleanupBlock();
5169
5170 // Strip away the noreturn attribute to better diagnose unreachable UB.
5171 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
5172 // Also remove from function since CallBase::hasFnAttr additionally checks
5173 // attributes of the called function.
5174 if (auto *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
5175 F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5176 CI->removeAttribute(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
5177 llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5178
5179 // Avoid incompatibility with ASan which relies on the `noreturn`
5180 // attribute to insert handler calls.
5181 if (SanOpts.hasOneOf(SanitizerKind::Address |
5182 SanitizerKind::KernelAddress)) {
5183 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5184 llvm::IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPGuard(Builder);
5185 Builder.SetInsertPoint(CI);
5186 auto *FnType = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
5187 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn =
5188 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FnType, "__asan_handle_no_return");
5189 EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn);
5190 }
5191 }
5192
5193 EmitUnreachable(Loc);
5194 Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
5195
5196 // FIXME: For now, emit a dummy basic block because expr emitters in
5197 // generally are not ready to handle emitting expressions at unreachable
5198 // points.
5199 EnsureInsertPoint();
5200
5201 // Return a reasonable RValue.
5202 return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
5203 }
5204
5205 // Perform the swifterror writeback.
5206 if (swiftErrorTemp.isValid()) {
5207 llvm::Value *errorResult = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorTemp);
5208 Builder.CreateStore(errorResult, swiftErrorArg);
5209 }
5210
5211 // Emit any call-associated writebacks immediately. Arguably this
5212 // should happen after any return-value munging.
5213 if (CallArgs.hasWritebacks())
5214 emitWritebacks(*this, CallArgs);
5215
5216 // The stack cleanup for inalloca arguments has to run out of the normal
5217 // lexical order, so deactivate it and run it manually here.
5218 CallArgs.freeArgumentMemory(*this);
5219
5220 // Extract the return value.
5221 RValue Ret = [&] {
5222 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
5223 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
5224 auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
5225
5226 Address addr = SRetPtr;
5227 addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
5228
5229 assert(CI->getType() == RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType());
5230 bool requiresExtract = isa<llvm::StructType>(CI->getType());
5231
5232 unsigned unpaddedIndex = 0;
5233 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
5234 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
5235 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
5236 Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
5237 llvm::Value *elt = CI;
5238 if (requiresExtract)
5239 elt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(elt, unpaddedIndex++);
5240 else
5241 assert(unpaddedIndex == 0);
5242 Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
5243 }
5244 // FALLTHROUGH
5245 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5246 }
5247
5248 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
5249 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
5250 RValue ret = convertTempToRValue(SRetPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
5251 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5252 PopCleanupBlock();
5253 return ret;
5254 }
5255
5256 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
5257 // If we are ignoring an argument that had a result, make sure to
5258 // construct the appropriate return value for our caller.
5259 return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
5260
5261 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
5262 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
5263 llvm::Type *RetIRTy = ConvertType(RetTy);
5264 if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == RetIRTy && RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
5265 switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
5266 case TEK_Complex: {
5267 llvm::Value *Real = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 0);
5268 llvm::Value *Imag = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 1);
5269 return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(Real, Imag));
5270 }
5271 case TEK_Aggregate: {
5272 Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
5273 bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
5274
5275 if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
5276 DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "agg.tmp");
5277 DestIsVolatile = false;
5278 }
5279 EmitAggregateStore(CI, DestPtr, DestIsVolatile);
5280 return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
5281 }
5282 case TEK_Scalar: {
5283 // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
5284 // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
5285 llvm::Value *V = CI;
5286 if (V->getType() != RetIRTy)
5287 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, RetIRTy);
5288 return RValue::get(V);
5289 }
5290 }
5291 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5292 }
5293
5294 Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
5295 bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
5296
5297 if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
5298 DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "coerce");
5299 DestIsVolatile = false;
5300 }
5301
5302 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
5303 Address StorePtr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, DestPtr, RetAI);
5304 CreateCoercedStore(CI, StorePtr, DestIsVolatile, *this);
5305
5306 return convertTempToRValue(DestPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
5307 }
5308
5309 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
5310 case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
5311 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
5312 }
5313
5314 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled ABIArgInfo::Kind");
5315 } ();
5316
5317 // Emit the assume_aligned check on the return value.
5318 if (Ret.isScalar() && TargetDecl) {
5319 AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter.EmitAsAnAssumption(Loc, RetTy, Ret);
5320 AllocAlignAttrEmitter.EmitAsAnAssumption(Loc, RetTy, Ret);
5321 }
5322
5323 // Explicitly call CallLifetimeEnd::Emit just to re-use the code even though
5324 // we can't use the full cleanup mechanism.
5325 for (CallLifetimeEnd &LifetimeEnd : CallLifetimeEndAfterCall)
5326 LifetimeEnd.Emit(*this, /*Flags=*/{});
5327
5328 if (!ReturnValue.isExternallyDestructed() &&
5329 RetTy.isDestructedType() == QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct)
5330 pushDestroy(QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct, Ret.getAggregateAddress(),
5331 RetTy);
5332
5333 return Ret;
5334}
